EntityDef.name: pmBatteryDepthOfDischargeDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of battery depth of discharge (DoD). [0]: Number of times battery voltage less than 40.8 V. [1]: Number of times battery voltage in range [40.8..41.9] V. [2]: Number of times battery voltage in range [42.0..43.1] V. [3]: Number of times battery voltage in range [43.2..44.3] V. [4]: Number of times battery voltage in range [44.4..45.4] V. [5]: Number of times battery voltage in range [45.5..46.8] V. [6]: Number of times battery voltage greater than 46.8 V.
Initial counter value is internal measurement results since battery installation. Counter is marked as suspect when attribute batteryInstallationDate of MO BatteryBackup is changed.

EntityDef.name: pmBatteryDischargeTimeDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distributed durations of battery discharges. PDF ranges: [0]: Number of battery discharges, duration less than 3 minutes. [1]: Number of battery discharges, duration in range [3..9] minutes. [2]: Number of battery discharges, duration in range [10..29] minutes. [3]: Number of battery discharges, duration in range [30..59] minutes. [4]: Number of battery discharges, duration in range [60..119] minutes. [5]: Number of battery discharges, duration in range [120..239] minutes. [6]: Number of battery discharges, duration in range [240..479] minutes. [7]: Number of battery discharges, duration greater than 479 minutes.
Initial counter value is internal measurement results since battery installation. Counter is marked as suspect when attribute batteryInstallationDate of MO BatteryBackup is changed.

EntityDef.name: pmBatteryMainLoadUnderVoltDiscTimeDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of battery discharge durations on the condition that main load is disconnected. [0]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration less than 3 minutes. [1]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration in range [3..9] minutes. [2]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration in range [10..29] minutes. [3]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration in range [30..59] minutes. [4]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration in range [60..119] minutes. [5]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration in range [120..239] minutes. [6]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration in range [240..479] minutes. [7]: Number of main load disconnection, where battery discharge duration greater than 479 minutes.
Initial counter value is internal measurement results since battery installation. Counter is marked as suspect when attribute batteryInstallationDate of MO BatteryBackup is changed.

EntityDef.name: pmBatteryTemperatureDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of battery operating temperatures. PDF ranges: [0]: Minutes when temperature less than -5 Celsius degrees. [1]: Minutes when temperature in range [-5..-1] Celsius degrees. [2]: Minutes when temperature in range [0..4] Celsius degrees. [3]: Minutes when temperature in range [5..9] Celsius degrees. [4]: Minutes when temperature in range [10..14] Celsius degrees. [5]: Minutes when temperature in range [15..19] Celsius degrees. [6]: Minutes when temperature in range [20..24] Celsius degrees. [7]: Minutes when temperature in range [25..29] Celsius degrees. [8]: Minutes when temperature in range [30..34] Celsius degrees. [9]: Minutes when temperature in range [35..39] Celsius degrees. [10]: Minutes when temperature in range [40..44] Celsius degrees. [11]: Minutes when temperature in range [45..49] Celsius degrees. [12]: Minutes when temperature in range [50..54] Celsius degrees. [13]: Minutes when temperature in range [55..59] Celsius degrees. [14]: Minutes when temperature in range [60..64] Celsius degrees. [15]: Minutes when temperature in range [65..69] Celsius degrees. [16]: Minutes when temperature greater than 70 Celsius degrees.
Initial counter value is internal measurement results since battery installation. Counter is marked as suspect when attribute batteryInstallationDate of MO BatteryBackup is changed.

The bytes belonging to the Initialization Vector (IV), which are part of the ESB payload but not encrypted, are not counted.

EntityDef.name: pmOutDiscNoSa

EntityDef.name: pmOutEspData

The bytes belonging to the Initialization Vector (IV), which are part of the ESB payload but not encrypted, are not counted.

EntityDef.name: pmOutPkt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing packets for the tunnel.

EntityDef.name: pmDot1qTpVlanPortInFrames
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of valid frames received on this port, belonging to this VLAN and IP interface. If there are more than one IP interface belonging to the same VLAN, the total number of frames for a specific VLAN is the sum of the pmDot1qTpVlanPortInFrames counter for all IP interfaces belonging to the VLAN. The counter is also used for number of un-tagged frames received from the LAN associated with the IP interface.

EntityDef.name: pmDot1qTpVlanPortOutFrames
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of valid frames transmitted from this port, belonging to this VLAN and IP interface. If there is more than one IP interface belonging to the same VLAN, the total number of frames for a VLAN is the sum of the pmDot1qTpVlanPortOutFrames counter for all IP interfaces belonging to this VLAN. The counter is also counts the number of untagged frames received from the LAN associated with the IP interface.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpInMcastOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received IP multicast octets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpInMcastPkts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received IP multicast packets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpOutMcastOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of sent IP multicast octets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpOutMcastPkts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of sent IP multicast packets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsIpAddrErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received IP datagrams discarded due to invalid header address.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsIpInDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received IP datagrams discarded due to resource problems (for example, lack of buffer space)

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsIpInHdrErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received IP datagrams with an error in the header.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsIpInReceives
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received IP datagrams, including those with errors.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsIpOutDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of IP datagrams that should be sent, but which were discarded due to resource problems (for example, lack of buffer space).

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsIpOutRequests
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of IP datagrams requested by the IP user protocol to be processed for sending.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsIpUnknownProtos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of locally addressed IP datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

EntityDef.name: pmInDiscPolicy
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the IP interface that match a policy rule with the action, discard.

EntityDef.name: pmInEsp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the IP interface with protocol ESP.

EntityDef.name: pmInPassedPolicy
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the IP interface that match a policy rule with the action, pass.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCInOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received IP octets, including those with errors.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCInReceives
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received IP datagrams, including those with errors.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCOutOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of transmitted IP octets.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCOutTransmits
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of transmitted IP datagrams.

EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed pings toward defaultRouter1.

EntityDef.name: pmDot1qTpVlanPortInDiscardsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of valid frames discarded on the link, for reasons related to VLAN (for example, the VLAN id is not configured).

EntityDef.name: pmIfInBroadcastPktsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the link, with a broadcast address delivered to a higher sub-layer.

EntityDef.name: pmIfInDiscardsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received packets discarded on the link, due to lack of resources (for example, buffer space).

EntityDef.name: pmIfInErrorsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the link that were discarded due to errors found in the packets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfInMulticastPktsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets on the link, delivered by this sublayer to a higher layer that were addressed to a multicast address at this sublayer.

EntityDef.name: pmIfInOctetsLink1Hi
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of octets received on the link, including framing characters.
The high-capacity counter for received octets on an interface is in two parts. This counter represents the higher part of the 62 least-significant bits of the high-capacity counter for received octets. The two most-significant bits of this 64-bit counter are discarded. This counter is presented as: pmIfInOctetsLinkxHi (bits 61-31) and pmIfInOctetsLinkxLo (bits 30-0).

EntityDef.name: pmIfInOctetsLink1Lo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counter represents the lower part of the 62 least-significant bits of the high-capacity counter as described in pmIfInOctetsLink1Hi.

EntityDef.name: pmIfInUcastPktsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of incoming unicast Ethernet frames on the link.

EntityDef.name: pmIfInUnknownProtosLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the link with a protocol that is not supported or is unknown.

EntityDef.name: pmIfOutBroadcastPktsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of outgoing broadcast Ethernet frames requested to be transmitted on the link (including those that were discarded or not sent).

EntityDef.name: pmIfOutDiscardsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets requested to be transmitted on the link, but which were discarded due to lack of resources (for example, buffer space).

EntityDef.name: pmIfOutErrorsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets requested to be transmitted on the link, but which were discarded due to errors found in the packets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfOutMulticastPktsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of outgoing multicast Ethernet frames requested to be transmitted on the link (including those that were discarded or not sent).

EntityDef.name: pmIfOutOctetsLink1Hi
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of octets transmitted on the link, including framing characters.
The high-capacity counter for transmitted octets on an interface is in two parts. This counter represents the higher part of the 62 least-significant bits of the high-capacity counter for transmitted octets. The two most-significant bits of this 64-bit counter are discarded. This counter is presented as: pmIfOutOctetsLinkxHi (bits 61-31) and pmIfOutOctetsLinkxLo (bits 30-0).

EntityDef.name: pmIfOutOctetsLink1Lo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counter represents the lower part of the 62 least-significant bits of the high-capacity counter as described in pmIfOutOctetsLink1Hi.

EntityDef.name: pmIfOutUcastPktsLink1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of outgoing unicast Ethernet frames requested to be transmitted on the link (including those that were discarded or not sent).

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInDestUnreachs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received ICMP Destination Unreachable messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInEchoReps
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received ICMP Echo Reply messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInEchos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received ICMP Echo Request messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of ICMP messages discarded due to ICMP header error (that is, bad checksum or length field) or when the ICMP message has an unsupported type value.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInMsgs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of received ICMP messages regardless of its type and code.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInParamProbs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received ICMP messages indicating Parameter Problem.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInRedirects
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received ICMP Redirect messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInSrcQuenchs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received ICMP Source Quench messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpInTimeExcds
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received ICMP Time Exceeded messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpOutDestUnreachs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of sent ICMP Destination Unreachable messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpOutEchoReps
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of sent ICMP Echo Reply messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpOutEchos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of sent ICMP Echo Request messages.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpOutMsgs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of sent ICMP messages regardless of its type and code.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFragCreates
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of IP fragments that are generated as a result of fragmentation at this entity.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFragFails
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of IP datagrams which need to be fragmented, but which cannot be, e g due to that their "Don't Fragment" flag is set.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFragOks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of IP datagrams which are successfully fragmented at this entity.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpInAddrErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received IP packets where the packet source IP address is either a Broadcast address or a Multicast address.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpInDelivers
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of recevied IP packets that was successfully terminated and delivered to higher level protocols.
The counter is increased by one for every 1000 packets. This value is zero if less than 1000 packets are counted.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpInHdrErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received packets discarded due to errors in the IP header, that is: - The checksum of the IP header is faulty. Note that the check is only done when the length of the header is larger than 5, i.e. the packet contains options. In case the header length is 5 the check is performed by the IpInterface, compare with the pmIfStatsIpInHdrErrors counter.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpInReceives
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of IP packets received by the host regardless of encapsulated protocol. This also includes faulty packets which have been discarded. The counter is increased by one for every 1000 packets. This value is zero if less than 1000 packets are counted.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpInUnknownProtos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received IP packets discarded by the host due to unknown or unsupported protocol.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpOutRequests
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of IP datagrams which local IP user protocols, including Internet Control Message Protocol (ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. This counter does not include any datagrams counted in ipForwDatagrams.
Counted at two locations. The counter is increased by one for every 1000 packets. This value is zero if less than 1000 packets are counted.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpPortUnreachable
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received IP packets that could not be delivered to a higher layer protocol, because of unresolved destination port number or because of unresolved TEID (Tunnel Endpoint Identifier) value.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpReasmFails
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc.).
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpReasmOks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of IP datagrams which are successfully reassembled.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmIpReasmReqds
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received fragments which are required to be reassembled at this entity.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmUdpInDatagrams
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received UDP datagrams delivered to higher level protocol/user, including datagrams received during session release.
It does not count UDP datagrams discarded due to unresolved port (pmUdpNoPorts), nor datagrams discarded due to bad checksum (pmUdpInErrors). The counter is increased by one for every 1000 packets. This value is zero if less than 1000 packets are counted.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmUdpInErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of received UDP datagrams that could not be delivered for reasons other than the lack of an application at the destination port, that is: - Incorrect UDP checksum. - The desired queue for payload towards the application is full. - UDP datagrams with length = 8, hence no data to deliver to the user. - Too large UDP datagram.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.name: pmUdpOutDatagrams
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of UDP datagrams sent to the IP protocol layer for encapsulation and transmission to the network. The counter is increased by one for every 1000 packets. This value is zero if less than 1000 packets are counted.
Only applicable for IPv4.

EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of octets that have been dropped instead of enqueued by the queue manager. Both headers and payload are counted.

EntityDef.name: pmQueueDroppedPackets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets that have been dropped instead of enqueued by the queue manager.

EntityDef.name: pmQueueOutOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of octets in both headers and payload, transmitted from the queue.

EntityDef.name: pmQueueOutPackets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets transmitted from the queue.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpInMcastOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received IP multicast octets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpInMcastPkts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received IP multicast packets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpOutMcastOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of sent IP multicast octets.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsHCIpOutMcastPkts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of sent IP multicast packets.

EntityDef.name: pmInDiscPolicy
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the interface that match a policy rule with the action, discard.

EntityDef.name: pmInPassedPolicy
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of packets received on the interface that match a policy rule with the action, pass.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCInOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received IP octets, including those with errors.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCInReceives
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received IP datagrams, including those with errors.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCOutOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of transmitted IP octets.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsHCOutTransmits
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of transmitted IP datagrams.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsInAddrErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of recived IP datagrams discarded, because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsInDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space).

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsInHdrErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received IP datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsInUnknownProtos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of locally-addressed IP datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsOutDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of IP datagrams that should be sent, but were discarded due to resource problems (for example, lack of buffer space).

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsOutFragCreates
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of output datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of IP fragmentation.
When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully fragmented datagram.

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsReasmFails
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of failures detected.
The number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc.).

EntityDef.name: pmIpIfStatsReasmReqds
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of IP fragments received that needed to be reassembled at this interface.
When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsDscpInOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Series of measurements recorded during a reporting period where each measurement is the number of octets in input IP packets received by the IPv4/IPv6 interface including those received with invalid address but excluding packets received with error in the IP header error using one of the DSCP values in the DSCP aggregation group during the measurement interval. Octets from packets in pmIfStatsDscpInPkts must be counted here. The first value in the range will show the current sampling interval.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsDscpInPkts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Series of measurements recorded during a reporting period where each measurement is the number of input IP packets received by the IPv4/IPv6 interface including those received with invalid address but excluding packets received with error in the IP header using one of the DSCP values in the DSCP aggregation group during the measurement interval. The first value in the range will show the current sampling interval.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsDscpOutOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Series of measurements recorded during a reporting period where each measurement is the number of octets in IP packets using one of the DSCP values in the DSCP aggregation group that the IPv4/IPv6 interface delivered to the lower layers for transmission during the measurement interval. Octets from packets in pmIfStatsDscpOutPkts must be counted here. The first value in the range will show the current sampling interval.

EntityDef.name: pmIfStatsDscpOutPkts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Series of measurements recorded during a reporting period where each measurement is the number of IP packets using one of the DSCP values in the DSCP aggregation group that the IPv4/IPv6 interface supplied to the lower layers for transmission during the measurement interval. The first value in the range will show the current sampling interval.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, which the node received, but determined as having ICMP-specific errors.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInMsgs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of ICMP messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node, which includes all those counted by pmIcmpStatsInErrors.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsDestUnreach
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsEchoRep
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsEchos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsNeighAdv
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Neighbor Advertisement messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsNeighSol
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Neighbor Solicit messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsParmProb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsRedir
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Redirect messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsRoutAdv
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Router Advertisement messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsRoutSol
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Router Solicit messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsTimeExcds
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsInPktsTooBig
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Packet Too Big messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, received by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, which this node did not send, due to problems discovered within ICMP, such as a lack of buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutMsgs
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of ICMP messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, which this node attempted to send. This counter includes all those counted by pmIcmpStatsOutErrors.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsDestUnreach
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Destination Unreachable messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsEchoRep
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Echo Reply messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsEchos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Echo (request) messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsNeighAdv
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Neighbor Advertisement messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsNeighSol
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Neighbor Solicitation messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsParmProb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Parameter Problem messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsRedir
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Redirect messages sent.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsRoutAdv
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Router Advertisement messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsRoutSol
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Router Solicit messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsTimeExcds
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Time Exceeded messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIcmpStatsOutPktsTooBig
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of ICMP Packet Too Big messages on the protocol version specified in the attribute icmpStatsIpVersion, sent by the node.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFlowInOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Series of measurements recorded during a reporting period, where each measurement is the number of octets in input IP packets received by the IPv4 or IPv6 interface from the specified IP address using one of the configured DSCP values but excluding packets received with error in the IP header during the sampling interval. Octets from packets in pmIpFlowInPkts must be counted here. The first value in the range will show the current sampling interval.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFlowMaxInBitrate
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The ingress IP-layer bitrate calculated for the highest measurement in pmIpFlowInOctets during a reporting period.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFlowMaxOutBitrate
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The egress IP-layer bitrate calculated for the highest measurement in pmIpFlowOutOctets during a reporting period.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFlowMinInBitrate
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The ingress IP-layer bitrate calculated for the lowest measurement in pmIpFlowInOctets during a reporting period.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFlowMinOutBitrate
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The egress IP-layer bitrate calculated for the lowest measurement in pmIpFlowOutOctets during a reporting period.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFlowOutOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Series of measurements recorded during a reporting period where each measurement is the number of octets in IP packets transmitted by the IPv4 or IPv6 interface towards specified IP address using one of the configured DSCP during the sampling interval. Octets from packets in pmIpFlowOutPkts must be counted here. The first value in the range will show the current sampling interval.

EntityDef.name: pmIpFlowOutPkts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Series of measurements recorded during a reporting period where each measurement is the number of IP packets transmitted by the IPv4 or IPv6 interface towards the specified IP using one of the configured DSCP values during the sampling interval. The first value in the range will show the current sampling interval.

EntityDef.name: pmMoFootprintMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counter specifies the current footprint in the eNB from the configured MO instances for all different Cell Relations and External Cells in relation to the MO system limit. The higher the value, the more internal memory is consumed in the eNB for MO instances for the different types of Cell Relations and External Cells. The value is the highest sampled value during a ROP period. When the value reaches 100, further creation attempts for MO instances are rejected.

EntityDef.name: pmPagS1Discarded

EntityDef.name: pmPagS1EdrxDiscarded

EntityDef.name: pmPagS1EdrxReceived

EntityDef.name: pmPagS1Received
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received S1AP Paging messages in the RBS. Non prioritized, prioritized S1AP Paging messages and eDRX paging messages are included.

EntityDef.name: pmRimAssocMax

EntityDef.name: pmPagS1DiscDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of S1AP Paging messages that are discarded (and not routed to any cell) due to that the maximum number of incoming S1AP Paging messages during a certain time interval is reached. This distribution counter is a subset of pmPagS1RecDistr and is per priority level. The counter is only valid if the feature Priority Paging is activated.
Ranges: [0]: No Priority level [1]: Priority level 1 [2]: Priority level 2 [3]: Priority level 3 [4]: Priority level 4 [5]: Priority level 5 [6]: Priority level 6 [7]: Priority level 7 [8]: Priority level 8

EntityDef.name: pmPagS1RecDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
This distribution counter counts the number of received S1AP Paging messages in the RBS per priority level. The counter is only valid if the feature Priority Paging is activated.
Ranges: [0]: No Priority level [1]: Priority level 1 [2]: Priority level 2 [3]: Priority level 3 [4]: Priority level 4 [5]: Priority level 5 [6]: Priority level 6 [7]: Priority level 7 [8]: Priority level 8

EntityDef.name: pmA3InterFBestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A3 inter-frequency measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmA3InterFBestCellEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A3 inter-frequency measurement reports with trigger quantity RSRP received.

EntityDef.name: pmA3InterFBestCellEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received A3 inter-frequency measurement reports for target cell measurements triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmA5BestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A5 measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmA5BestCellEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A5 measurement reports received with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmA5BestCellEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received A5 inter-frequency measurement reports for target cell measurements triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmAccessClassBarringEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter calculates the total time that feature Load-Based Access Barring has triggered Access Class Barring for Emergency calls in the cell.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveDrbDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of the contributions from each UE in the cell of the number of active DRBs in the downlink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveDrbUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of the contributions from each UE in the cell of the number of active DRBs in the uplink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Peak number of UEs considered active in the downlink direction, i.e. has designated data in UE dedicated buffer in the eNB. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs considered active in the downlink direction. For a carrier aggregation UE, is counted on Pcell.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDrbSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of active UE or active DRB measurement samples. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP)

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Peak number of UEs considered active in the uplink direction, i.e. the UE is considered to have data in its buffer. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs considered active in the uplink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmAdjustAccessDynLoadCtrl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter shows how long time within the ROP period that the cell load control window for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover) has been down regulated from its maximum value due to high procedure latency and/or high drop rate.

EntityDef.name: pmAdjustAccessMpLoadCtrl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter shows how long time within the ROP period that the DU or Baseband load control window for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover) has been down regulated from its maximum value due to high MP load.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrCandNrelCgiAdd
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of automatic neighbour relation candidates added by CGI report.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrCandNrelRem
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of automatic neighbour relation candidates removed.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrCandNrelX2Add
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of automatic neighbour relation candidates added by X2 procedure.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrHoSuccLevelLow
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of cell relations where the EUtranCellRelation::hoSuccLevel has changed from MEDIUM to LOW.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrHoSuccLevelMedium
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of cell relations where the EUtranCellRelation::hoSuccLevel has changed from HIGH to MEDIUM.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrNeighbrelAdd
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of neighbour relations added by the ANR function.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrNeighbrelRem
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of neighbour relations removed by the ANR function.

EntityDef.name: pmB2BestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total B2 measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmB2BestCellEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total B2 measurement reports received with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmB2BestCellEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received B2 measurement reports for target cell measurements triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of traffic Bad Coverage measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovOutSearchEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 measurement reports received because outer search zone is entered. Used when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is active.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovOutSearchEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 measurement reports received because outer search zone is entered with trigger quantity RSRP. Used when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is active.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovSearchEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of A2 measurement reports received due to entering the Search zone. This counter is used when the feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovSearchEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 measurement reports received because the search zone is entered with trigger quantity RSRP. This counter is used when the feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovSearchEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 event reports because the search zone threshold is entered with trigger quantity UL SINR. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBbUeMeasAllocAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to allocate an object from the internal memory pool dedicated to UE throughput measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmBbUeMeasAllocSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful object allocations from the internal memory pool dedicated to UE throughput measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmBestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of traffic Best Cell measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmCaCapableDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of carrier aggregation capable UE measurement samples.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of carrier aggregation configured UE measurement samples.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredMeasAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempted SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done based on coverage measurements. This includes changes of cells due to receiving an A6 report.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredMeasSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful SCell configurations, excluding RRC signaling to UE, when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done based on coverage measurements. This includes changes of cells due to receiving an A6 report.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredNoMeasAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempted SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done without using any coverage measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredNoMeasSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful SCell configurations, excluding RRC signaling to UE, when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done without using any coverage measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of 5-second samples of SCell configuration accumulations included in ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfigured
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of SCell deconfigurations, except when the same cell is deconfigured and configured as SCell in the same RRC message. Has subcounters for specific reasons for SCell deconfiguration.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfiguredLostCoverage
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Subcounter to pmCaDeconfigured. The number of SCell deconfigurations due to poor coverage in the SCell.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfiguredSCellChange
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Subcounter to pmCaDeconfigured. The number of SCell deconfigurations due to changing to another SCell.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfiguredSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of 5-second samples of SCell deconfiguration accumulations included in ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmCellAdmControlPdcchRej
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counter is stepped whenever we have a reject due to that pdcch is limiting new connections.

EntityDef.name: pmCellAdmControlPdcchRejMeas
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counter is stepped whenever we would have had a reject due to that pdcch is limiting new connections.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownLockAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled).

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownLockMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownUnlockMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been enabled.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDowntimeAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Length of time the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled). The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDowntimeMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Length of time the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily. The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFCsg

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFHybridCsg

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFUeMeas
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of outgoing intra-LTE, inter-frequency handover execution attempts based on A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement report.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFUeMeasRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of outgoing intra-LTE, inter-frequency handover execution attempts based on A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFUl

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraF

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover executions that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover executions that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraFTuneOut
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts made by Tune-out UEs

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers that was performed due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFUeMeas
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing intra-LTE, inter-frequency handovers execution based on A3 Inter-frequency or A5 measurement report.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFUeMeasRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing, intra-LTE, inter-frequency handovers execution based on A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency HOs, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handovers.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFAfterResync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful intra-LTE intra-frequency handovers after resync has been performed.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFTuneOut
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE intra frequency handovers made by Tune-out UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLowCovUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of handover preparation attempts to start outgoing intra LTE HO for low-coverage UE.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempts to start outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparation, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start intra LTE intra frequency handover preparation.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency, - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency, - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLowCovUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful HO preparations for outgoing intra LTE HO for low-coverage UE.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations that was performed due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparations, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handover preparations.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellSleepTime
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Time the cell has been disabled due to energy saving mode. The system sets cell MO OperationalState to Disabled and AvailabilityStatus to Off_duty. The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmConfigRejDlComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of measurement requests for Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point triggered by Layer 2 and rejected by Layer 3.

EntityDef.name: pmConfirmedUeRelReqPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times an RRC connection is released to IDLE, after a FAPPI message is received with DC field set to 0 from a PFT UE.

EntityDef.name: pmContDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the downlink direction due to lack of eNodeB resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContDlCapLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the downlink direction due to lack of DL capacity license.

EntityDef.name: pmContDlHw
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the downlink direction due to lack of hardware resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContDlPdcch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the downlink direction due to lack of PDCCH resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the uplink direction due to lack of eNodeB resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContUlCapLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the uplink direction due to lack of license resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContUlHw
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the uplink direction due to lack of hardware resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContUlPdcch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the uplink direction due to lack of PDCCH resources.

EntityDef.name: pmCovGoodZoneSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of measurement samples taken for the measurements of number of UEs considered to be in the coverage good zone. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated. Associated ACC pmCounter pmCovGoodZoneSum.

EntityDef.name: pmCovGoodZoneSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs considered to be in the radio coverage good zone because A2 search threshold has not been passed for any of the quality measures: DL RSRP, DL RSRQ, UL SINR. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCovSearchZoneSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of measurement samples taken for the measurements of number of UEs considered to be in the coverage search zone. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated. Associated ACC pmCounter pmCovSearchZoneSum.

EntityDef.name: pmCovSearchZoneSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs considered to be in the radio coverage search zone because A2 search threshold has been passed for any one, two or three of the radio coverage quality measures: DL RSRP, DL RSRQ, UL SINR. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCriticalBorderEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of A2 measurement reports received due to critical threshold is reached. This counter is used instead of pmBadCovEvalReport when the feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCriticalBorderEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 measurement reports received because critical threshold is reached with trigger quantity RSRP. Used when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is active.

EntityDef.name: pmCriticalBorderEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 event reports because the critical threshold is reached with trigger quantity UL SINR. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCrsIcCapableSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of CRS-IC-capable UE measurement samples.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsDetectedHarqNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast DL assignments sent during DRX onDuration and confirmed by corresponding HARQ ACK/NACK.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsDetectedHarqVolteNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast DL assignments that are transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs with bearer mapped to QCI with VoIP service type. Reception must be confirmed by corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block. DL assignments are excluded if this cell is SCell for those UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsTrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsTransNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast DL assignments transmitted during DRX onDuration.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsTransPCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsTransSCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as a secondary cell.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsTransVolte
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP. The DL assignments are excluded if this cell is a secondary cell for those UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsTransVolteNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast DL assignments transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs that have bearer mapped to QCI with VoIP service type. DL assignments are excluded if this cell is SCell for those UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithDetectedHarqAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments that are confirmed by detecting a corresponding HARQ-ACK.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithDetectedHarqAckPCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithDetectedHarqAckSCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs using this cell as a secondary cell, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithDetectedHarqAckVolte
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding ACK or NACK for any transport block. The DL assignments are excluded if this cell is a secondary cell for those UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithUnknownReception
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments for which the reception is unknown.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithUnknownReceptionPCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is unknown.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithUnknownReceptionSCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs using this cell as a secondary cell, for which the reception is unknown.

EntityDef.name: pmDlAssigsWithUnknownReceptionVolte
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast DL assignments that are transmitted to UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is unknown. The DL assignments are excluded if this cell is a secondary cell for those UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmDrxCommandPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a DRX Command MAC Control Element is sent to a PFT UE.

EntityDef.name: pmDrxSleepTime
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Contains the DRX sleep time in number of subframes for all UEs in the cell taking into consideration SR pending time (time between SR and UL grant).

EntityDef.name: pmDrxSleepTimePft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: DRX sleep time in number of subframes for all PFT UEs in the cell. DRX sleep time takes into consideration SR time between SR and UL grant.

EntityDef.name: pmDrxTotalTime
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Contains the DRX total time in number of subframes for all UEs in the cell.

EntityDef.name: pmDrxTotalTimePft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: DRX total time in number of subframes for all PFT UEs in the cell.

EntityDef.name: pmDsdReqPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a FAPPI message is received from a PFT UE, with the Delay Tolerant Data (DT) flag set to 0 (Delay Sensitive Data).

EntityDef.name: pmDtdReqPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a FAPPI message is received from a PFT UE, with the Delay Tolerant Data (DT) flag set to 1 (Delay Tolerant Data).

EntityDef.name: pmElcOffBadCov
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of triggering ELC off due to ELC bad coverage detection. Used when feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmElcPdcchBlankedTti
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of TTIs for which CRS:es in the PDCCH region are fully or partially blanked.

EntityDef.name: pmElcPdschBlankedTti
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of TTIs for which CRS:es in the PDSCH region are fully or partially blanked.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttAdded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of added E-RAB Establishment attempts. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttAddedHoOngoing
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed establishment attempts of added E-RABs due to ongoing handover. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttAddedPa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of added E-RAB Establishment attempts with Privileged Access. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttInit
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of initial E-RAB Establishment attempts. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttInitPa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of initial E-RAB Establishment attempts with Privileged Access. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabFailAddedLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed establishment of added E-RABs due to license rejects (Multiple Radio Bearer per user or RLC UM). Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabFailGbrDlEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed E-RAB setup attempts due to downlink GBR overload for resources common to the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabFailGbrUlEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed E-RAB setup attempts due to uplink GBR overload for resources common to the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabFailInitLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed establishment of initial E-RABs due to license rejects (Multiple Radio Bearer per user or RLC UM). Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccAdded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successfully added E-RABs. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccAddedPa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successfully added E-RABs with Privileged Access. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccInit
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful initial E-RAB Establishments. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccInitPa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful initial E-RAB Establishments with Privileged Access. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabLevSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of times the corresponding Sum counters has been incremented. Associated ACC pmCounter pmErabLevSum.

EntityDef.name: pmErabLevSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Sum of all sample values recorded for Number of simultaneous E-RABs

EntityDef.name: pmErabMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The peak number of simultaneous E-RAB usage.

EntityDef.name: pmErabModFailLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of E-RAB Modify attempts initiated from the MME which failed due to license reject.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases triggered by eNB per cell.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the eNB and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActCdt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically or by manual intervention) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActCdtAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActCdtAutoPnr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically) caused by a partial node restart or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal ERAB releases per cell by the eNB due to handover execution failure and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHoOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHoOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is a PFT UE, it is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHpr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal ERAB releases by the eNB per cell due to handover preparation and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHprOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover preparation failure. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHprOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover preparation failure. The UE is a PFT UE, it is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB. The UE is in Out-of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB. The UE is a PFT UE, it is in Out-of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActPe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases per cell, initiated by the RBS due to UE pre-emption with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed and when data was in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActTnFail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell due to S1 Interface Down, X2 Interface Down, or Transport Resource Unavailable. Preconditions are that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed and there is data in the UL or DL buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActUeLost
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal ERAB releases by the eNB per cell due that the contact with the UE is lost with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActUeLostOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActUeLostOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is a PFT UE, it is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbCdt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically or by manual intervention) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbCdtAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbCdtAutoPnr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell due to: - cell down time caused by a partial node restart (initiated automatically) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbExtIat
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases that occurred during the extended inactivity time, triggered by the eNB for each cell.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases per cell by the eNB due to handover execution failure.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHoOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHoOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHpr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by the eNB per cell due to handover preparation.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHprOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover preparation failure. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHprOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover preparation failure. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS due to license reject (per cell).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB. The UE is in Out-of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbPe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell, initiated by the RBS due to UE pre-emption with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbSir
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB due to software initiated release. Occurs when a UE Context is identified as hanging.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbTnFail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell due to S1 Interface Down, X2 Interface Down or Transport Resource Unavailable. A precondition is that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbUeLost
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by the eNB per cell due to that the contact with the UE is lost with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbUeLostOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbUeLostOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME with a cause regarded as abnormal.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME considered as abnormal. The counter is stepped if there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeExtIat
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME that occurred during the extended inactivity time and that had a cause regarded as abnormal.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME (per cell) and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeActEutra
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB Releases per cell, initiated by the MME with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active) and the cause was "Release due to EUtran generated reason".

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeActHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME during handover when there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeActUnspecified
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB Releases per cell, initiated by the MME with the pre-condition that the Initial Context Establishment procedure must first have been successfully completed and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active) and the cause was "Unspecified".

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeCellUnavail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the MME with the cause cell unavailable possibly due to S1 Reset. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME during handover.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of normal E-RAB Releases triggered by eNB per cell.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of normal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by the eNB and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbUserInactivity
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB releases by the eNB due to User inactivity.

EntityDef.name: pmErabResumeArpLow
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that the low ARP prioritized DRB are resumed.

EntityDef.name: pmFastPucchAssignPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a fast PUCCH assignment message is sent to a PFT UE.

EntityDef.name: pmGoodCovSearchEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A1 measurement reports received because good coverage zone is entered. Used when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is active.

EntityDef.name: pmGoodCovSearchEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A1 measurement reports received because good coverage zone is entered with trigger quantity RSRP. Used when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is active.

EntityDef.name: pmGoodCovSearchEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A1 event reports received because the good UL coverage zone is entered with trigger quantity UL SINR. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepOutS1RejInvalidInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of handover preparation failures that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency, - to closed access mode CSG cell and - caused by UE's CSG membership fail.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepOutS1RejInvalidInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of handover preparation failures that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency, - to Hybrid CSG cell and - caused by UE's CSG membership fail.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepOutS1RejInvalidIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of handover preparation failures that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency, - to closed access mode CSG cell and - caused by UE's CSG membership fail.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepOutS1RejInvalidIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of handover preparation failures that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency, - to Hybrid CSG cell and - caused by UE's CSG membership fail.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInBearerAdmissionRej
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Incoming Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to the fact that all the UE's bearers are rejected during bearer admission.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInCellIntensDLC
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed handover preparations due to cell connection intensity control regulated by Dynamic Load Control.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInCellIntensStat
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed handover preparations due to static cell connection intensity control.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInCellIntensSwC
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of failed handover preparations in the cell due to high SW component load on cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInCellLatency
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed handover preparations due to Procedure Latency Supervision.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInDlOnlyCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to the target cell being a downlink-only cell (EUtranCellFDD.isDlOnly = TRUE)

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInDuIntens
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed Handover preparations due to DU or Baseband connection intensity control.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInDuSwC
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of failed handover preparations due to high DU or Baseband SW component load.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInDynUeAdmCtrl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of non-privileged incoming handovers rejected by Dynamic UE Admission Control.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInHighLoad
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to high load.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInLicConnUsers
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to license for connected users being exceeded.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInLicLowCovUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of rejected incoming HO preparation messages, sent by target eNodeB due to lack of license for handover for low-coverage UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInLicMob
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Incoming Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to lack of license for handover.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInLicMultiErab
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of non-admitted E-RABs at an incoming handover preparation procedure, due to license for Multiple E-RAB being exceeded.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInLicRlcUm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of non-admitted E-RABs at an incoming handover preparation procedure, due to lack of license for RLC UM.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInMISigQCong
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed Incoming Handovers due to RAC-BB signal queue congestion.
