EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInMpOverload
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed handover preparations triggered by the MP overload state.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInOffloadAdmission
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counter specifies the number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to Offload Admission in the target cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInOverload
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNB due to cell overload.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInSl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Handover Preparation Failure messages sent by the target eNodeB due to cell in soft lock state

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInUlThres
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of handover preparations that failed due to that the target cell UL quality is bad. The HO preparation attempt may be triggered both by UL and DL measurements. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepRejInUlThresCaRedirect
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of CA-triggered redirects rejected because UL quality in target cell was insufficient.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPreventedNotInPlmnWL
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total HO, intra-frequency and inter-frequency, prevented prior to Handover Preparation because the target cell's PLMN are not whitelisted in the serving cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPreventedProblematicCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total HO, intra-frequency and inter-frequency, prevented prior to Handover Preparation because the target cell is identified as a problematic cell.

EntityDef.name: pmIdleModeRelDistrHighLoad
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a frequency is prioritized as target for cell reselection during idle mode at high load.

EntityDef.name: pmIdleModeRelDistrLowLoad
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a frequency is prioritized as target for cell reselection during idle mode at low load.

EntityDef.name: pmIdleModeRelDistrLowMediumLoad
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a frequency is prioritized as target for cell reselection during idle mode at low-medium load.

EntityDef.name: pmIdleModeRelDistrMediumHighLoad
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a frequency is prioritized as target for cell reselection during idle mode at medium-high load.

EntityDef.name: pmIdleModeRelDistrMediumLoad
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a frequency is prioritized as target for cell reselection during idle mode at medium load.

EntityDef.name: pmInSyncTimePft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: In-Sync time in number of subframes for all PFT UEs in the cell.

EntityDef.name: pmInactiveUeRelInHighLoad
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of inactive UEs released at handover when the MP load level is at least the value of the attribute releaseInactiveUesMpLoadLevel.

EntityDef.name: pmInvalidPftMsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of PFT messages received with an unknown PFT Message Type.

EntityDef.name: pmInvalidPftNum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of PFT messages received with an invalid PFT number.

EntityDef.name: pmLaaCapableDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of LAA carrier aggregation capable UE measurement samples.

EntityDef.name: pmLaaConfigurableDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UE measurement samples.

EntityDef.name: pmLbEvalExpiredUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of times connected UEs are evaluated to perform load balancing measurements. The selection of UEs is based on lbUeEvaluationTimer expiry.

EntityDef.name: pmLbSubRatioSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of load balancing cycles during the ROP. This together with the counter pmLbSubRatioSum can be used to calculate an average subscription ratio.

EntityDef.name: pmLbSubRatioSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the subscription ratio as the result of the traffic load assessment at every load balancing cycle. The values are accumulated each ROP, allowing the average subscription ratio to be presented for each period.

EntityDef.name: pmLongDrxCommandPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a Long DRX Command MAC Control Element is sent to a PFT UE.

EntityDef.name: pmMacCellThpTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: DL transfer time, measured in ms, when MAC layer transmission in DL is needed for at least one DRB in the cell. This includes buffer waiting times and possible HARQ retransmission delays. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. DL MAC transfer time over all carriers is incremented once on the PCell. This is suitable for PDCP timebase.

EntityDef.name: pmMacCellThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The transfer time used for UL Cell throughput. It consists of the number of ms in which there is need for DRB transmission for at least one UE in the cell. The transfer time includes buffer delay and time for possible HARQ retransmissions

EntityDef.name: pmMacDelayTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Aggregated time for the downlink MAC delay measure. The time for each sample shall show the time between reception from RLC until it is successfully received in the UE or HARQ failure occurs.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAck16qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 16QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAck256qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the DL direction using a 256QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAck64qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 64QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAckComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction where a dSINR from DL CoMP was applied in the Link Adaptation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAckQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a QPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlDtx16qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of occasions when a downlink HARQ feedback for a transport block using 16QAM modulation was not received from an UE and DTX is considered the reason.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlDtx256qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of occasions when DL HARQ feedback for a transport block using 256QAM modulation was not received from a UE, and DTX is considered the reason.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlDtx64qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of occasions when a downlink HARQ feedback for a transport block using 64QAM modulation was not received from an UE and DTX is considered the reason.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlDtxQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of occasions when a downlink HARQ feedback for a transport block using QPSK modulation was not received from an UE and DTX is considered the reason.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlNack16qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 16QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlNack256qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the DL direction using a 256QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlNack64qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a 64QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlNackComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction where a dSINR from DL CoMP was applied in the Link Adaptation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlNackQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a QPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqFail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of complete HARQ failures. When a HARQ transmission has reached maximum number of retransmissions, it will not be retransmitted again and is regarded as a scheduling activity complete HARQ failure.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlDtx16qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of occasions when an uplink grant was meant for HARQ transmission of a transport block using 16QAM modulation in the uplink direction, where DTX is considered the reason for no reception of HARQ in uplink in the eNB.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlDtx64Qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of DTX detections in UL related to data that is scheduled for 64-QAM.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlDtxQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of occasions when an uplink grant was meant for HARQ transmission of a transport block using QPSK modulation in the uplink direction, where DTX is considered the reason for no reception of HARQ in uplink in the eNB.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlFail16qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a 16QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlFail64Qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the UL direction that use a 64-QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlFailQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a QPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlSucc16qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a 16QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlSucc64Qam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful HARQ transmissions in the UL direction that use a 64-QAM modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqUlSuccQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the uplink direction using a QPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlDrxNoSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts used for DL MAC latency measurements that arrive when the UE is in DRX inactivity period and in UL Out-of-sync state.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlDrxNoSyncSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX inactivity period and in UL Out-of-sync state. It is accumulated over all DRBs with QCIs in the given range.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlDrxSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts used for DL MAC latency measurements that arrive when the UE is in DRX inactivity period and in UL In-sync state.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlDrxSyncSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX inactivity period and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all DRBs with QCIs in the given range.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlNoDrxSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts used for DL MAC latency measurements that arrive when the UE is in DRX activity period and in UL In-sync state.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlNoDrxSyncSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX activity period and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all DRBs with QCIs in the given range.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets for DL MAC latency measurements for the QCIs in the given range.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeQciDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time accumulated over all DRBs with QCIs in the given range.
The range of the QCIs included into the measurement is given by the MOM parameters minQciLatencyMeas and maxQciLatencyMeas.

EntityDef.name: pmMacUeThpTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: DL transfer time, measured in ms, when MAC layer transmission in DL is needed on at least one DRB for the UE. This includes buffer waiting times and possible HARQ retransmission delays. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. DL MAC transfer time over all carriers is incremented once on the PCell. This is suitable for PDCP timebase.

EntityDef.name: pmMacUeThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Transfer time used for UL UE throughput. Comprised of the number of ms in which there is need for transmission on at least one of the LCGs specified in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::includeLcgInMacUeThp. Transfer time includes buffer delay and time for possible HARQ retransmissions. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transfer time over all carriers is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmMacUeThpVolDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: DL MAC SDU volume transmitted on all DRBs for each UE. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. DL MAC transmitted volume over all carriers is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmMacUeThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Volume used for UL UE throughput. Consists of the MAC SDU volume received for the LCGs specified in EUtranCellFDD/EUtranCellTDD::includeLcgInMacUeThp. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transmitted volume over all carriers is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmMeasGapFailLicInterFOtdoa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Indicates the number of times a UE requests a measurement gap for Inter-Frequency OTDOA start or stop and is rejected as no valid license is issued.

EntityDef.name: pmMeasMissingNeighRel
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counter is stepped when Mobility performs no mobility actions due to no valid re-direct target existing. Thus it covers missing neighbor relations for IRAT Handovers and is not a general count of all missing neighbor relations.

EntityDef.name: pmMeasRep
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of measurement reports received from the UE.

EntityDef.name: pmMeasRepBadCovElc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of A2 measurement reports received due to ELC bad coverage detection. Used when feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmMeasRepDiscDlComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of measurement reports for Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point discarded by Layer 3.

EntityDef.name: pmMeasRepDlComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of measurement reports received from the UE with event A5 used in Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point.

EntityDef.name: pmMeasRepGoodCovElc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of A1 measurement reports received due to ELC good coverage detection. Used when feature Ericsson Lean Carrier is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmMimoSleepOppTime
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Reports the amount of time in seconds the cell has the opportunity to remain in MIMO sleep state.

EntityDef.name: pmMimoSleepTime
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Reports the amount of time in seconds the cell is in MIMO sleep state.

EntityDef.name: pmNasTransferAttAbortDlSrb2
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of downlink NAS transfer procedure on SRB2 aborted due to other event receiving such as measurement report, RRC Connection re-establishment, CS Fallback and other reason.

EntityDef.name: pmNasTransferAttDlSrb2
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of downlink NAS transfer procedure attempts on SRB2.

EntityDef.name: pmNasTransferFailPnrDlSrb2
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of DL NAS transfers on SRB2 forced-stopped due to partial node restart.

EntityDef.name: pmNasTransferSuccDlSrb2
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of downlink NAS transfer procedures on SRB2 successfully completed.

EntityDef.name: pmOocNewDataUlGrants
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Incremented for each UE in state Out Of Coverage (OOC), for each UL grant designated a new data transmissions (i.e. excluding retransmissions).

EntityDef.name: pmOocStateEntries
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Incremented each time a UE enters the state Out Of Coverage (OOC). Trigger for state entry is based on UL measurements indicating poor reception.

EntityDef.name: pmOocStateExits
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Incremented each time a UE exits the state Out Of Coverage (OOC). Trigger for state exit is based on UL measurements indicating good reception.

EntityDef.name: pmOocStateExitsUeRel
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Incremented at UE release if UE is in state Out Of Coverage (OOC).

EntityDef.name: pmOocUesLevSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Sum of recorded sample values for number of UEs in Out Of Coverage (OOC) state.

EntityDef.name: pmOutOfSyncTimePft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Out-of-Sync time in number of subframes for all PFT UEs in the cell.

EntityDef.name: pmPagDiscarded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of S1AP Paging messages discarded and not broadcasted in this cell. This counter is a subset of pmPagReceived. Both non prioritized, prioritized S1AP Paging messages and eDRX pagings are included.

EntityDef.name: pmPagEdrxDiscarded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of S1AP eDRX Paging messages discarded and not broadcasted in this cell. This counter is a subset of pmPageDRXReceived.

EntityDef.name: pmPagEdrxReceived
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of S1AP eDRX Paging messages routed to this cell. This counter is a subset of pmPagReceived.

EntityDef.name: pmPagReceived
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of S1AP Paging messages routed to this cell. Both non prioritized, prioritized S1AP Paging and eDRX paging messages are included.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceActivity
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counter of how often the PDCCH has 1 or more CCEs used. To re-normalize pmPdcchCceUtil for subframes containing traffic, use this counter compute and remove idle subframes.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchMaxCceAvail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total maximum number of CCEs available determined based on the bandwidth, antenna configuration and setting of CFI.
The value of the counter depends on the FDD/TDD configuration and in TDD also the special subframe configuration.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchResyncAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of attempted 3GPP procedure "PDCCH ordered resynchronization", see 3GPP TS 36.321 and TS 36.212. The counter is increased when a PDCCH ordered re-synchronization is sent in downlink.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchResyncFail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of 3GPP procedures where PDCCH ordered resynchronization but resulted in failure. See 3GPP TS 36.321 and TS 36.212.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchResyncSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful 3GPP procedures "PDCCH ordered resynchronization", see 3GPP TS 36.321 and TS 36.212.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchTxAggressive
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of aggressive unicast PDCCH transmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchTxConservative
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of conservative unicast PDCCH transmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpBitrateDlDrbMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Peak cell DL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpBitrateDlDrbMin
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Minimum cell DL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpBitrateUlDrbMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Peak cell UL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been received in the uplink direction, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpBitrateUlDrbMin
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Minimum cell UL bit rate. One cell bit rate sample is obtained by dividing the total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers aggregated to cell level, that has been received in the uplink direction, with the time (in seconds) of the sample gathering period.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatPktTransDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets for downlink Latency measurements.
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatPktTransDlDrxNoSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets for downlink Latency measurements when DRX is active and the UE has UL synchronization status "NOT synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatPktTransDlDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets for downlink Latency measurements when DRX is active and the UE has UL synchronization status "synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatPktTransDlNoDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets for downlink Latency measurements when DRX is NOT active and the UE has UL synchronization status "synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Aggregated DL Latency for a measurement period. The effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering the buffer until the first data has been transmitted to the UE.
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatTimeDlDrxNoSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Aggregated DL Latency when DRX is active and the UE has UL synchronization status "NOT synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatTimeDlDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Aggregated DL Latency when DRX is active and the UE has UL synchronization status "synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatTimeDlNoDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Aggregated DL Latency when DRX is NOT active and the UE has UL synchronization status "synchronized".
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlAqm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to Active Queue Management (AQM).
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to AQM is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in downlink due to handover and reestablishment procedures.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in the downlink due to handover and reestablishment procedures is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlPelr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) for which no part has been transmitted over the air in the downlink that are discarded due to reasons other than handover or active queue management.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to reasons other than handover or active queue management is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlPelrUu
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air in the downlink direction but not positively acknowledged, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done, due to reasons other than handover. Only applicable to DRB packets.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air in the downlink direction but not positively acknowledged, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done, due to reasons other than handover, is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktFwdDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) forwarded to target cell at handover for downlink sessions.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktLostUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) lost in the uplink.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktLostUlLimitations
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of lost packets in UL due to PDCP capacity limitations.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktPdbUlOkVoip
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Radio Link Control (RLC) Service Data Units (SDU), that is PDCP SDUs, in UL that are received within the PDB in uplink. Only applicable for VoIP. Note: If ROHC is enabled, pmPdcpPktPdbUlOkVoip might be greater than pmPdcpPktReceivedUlQci due to difference in ROHC control packets handling between the counters.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktReceivedDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received by RBS in PDCP in the downlink.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received by RBS in PDCP in the downlink is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktReceivedUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) received in the uplink.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktTransDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) successfully transmitted (RLC acknowledged by UE) in the downlink.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) successfully transmitted (RLC acknowledged by UE) in the downlink is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbCa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (UM and AM) in the downlink direction of carrier aggregation UE.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbLastTTI
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction in the last TTI when a buffer is emptied.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction in the last TTI when a buffer is emptied is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbLastTTICa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers of carrier aggregation UE that has been transferred (acknowledged by the carrier aggregation UE) in the downlink direction in the last TTI when a buffer is emptied.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransPlmn0
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN0.
PLMN0 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId located on ENodeBFunction.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN0 is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransPlmn1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN1.
PLMN1 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[0] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN1 is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransPlmn2
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN2.
PLMN2 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[1] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN2 is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransPlmn3
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN3.
PLMN3 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[2] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN3 is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransPlmn4
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN4.
PLMN4 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[3] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN4 is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransPlmn5
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN5.
PLMN5 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[4] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN5 is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransPlmn6
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN6.
PLMN6 refers to an unexpected PLMN, that is, a PLMN that cannot be associated with any PLMN configured in the ENodeBFunction or cell.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer for the UEs served by PLMN6 is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlSrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of bits (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction.
SRB0 volume is not included in this counter.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total number of bits (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the UE) in the downlink direction is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlSrbTrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Signalling Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer is measured on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction and transmitted over the GTP-U.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbPlmn0
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN0.
PLMN0 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute eNodeBPlmnId located on ENodeBFunction.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbPlmn1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN1.
PLMN1 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[0] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbPlmn2
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN2.
PLMN2 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[1] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbPlmn3
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN3.
PLMN3 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[2] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbPlmn4
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN4.
PLMN4 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[3] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbPlmn5
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN5.
PLMN5 refers to the PLMN configured in the attribute additionalPlmnList[4] located on EUtranCellFDD or EUtranCellTDD.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbPlmn6
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been received in the uplink direction for the UEs served by PLMN6.
PLMN6 refers to an unexpected PLMN, that is, a PLMN that cannot be associated with any PLMN configured in the ENodeBFunction or cell.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlSrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of bits (PDCP SDU) on Signaling Radio Bearers that has been transferred (acknowledged by the RBS) in the uplink direction.
SRB0 volume is not included in this counter.

EntityDef.name: pmPftEstablishedSession
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of successfully established PFT sessions.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbAvailDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs available for transmission in the downlink.
The value of the counter depends on the FDD/TDD configuration and in TDD also the special subframe configuration.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbAvailDlMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of Physical Resource Blocks (PRB) available for MBMS transmission in the downlink.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbAvailUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs available for transmission in the uplink.
The value of the counter depends on the FDD/TDD configuration.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlAilgHighPrio
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of PRB pairs generated by Air Interface Load Generator in the DL direction for load of higher priority than the real UEs load

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlAilgTot
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of PRB pairs generated by Air Interface Load Generator in DL for artificial load, both for high and low priority load.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlBcch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for System Information.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlDtch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for Data Radio Bearers (DRB) in the downlink.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlFirstTrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of PRB pairs used in DL for HARQ initial transmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum (high-water mark) value of DL PRB capacity usage.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlPcch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for paging.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlReTrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of PRB pairs used in DL for HARQ retransmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of measured samples of DL PRB capacity usage.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlSrbFirstTrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs for HARQ initial transmissions used for Signaling Radio Bearers (SRB) in the downlink.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Accumulated sum of DL PRB capacity usage.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedUlAilgTot
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of PRB pairs generated by Air Interface Load Generator in UL for artificial load, both for high and low priority load

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedUlDtch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for Data Radio Bearers (DRB) in the uplink.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedUlMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum (high-water mark) value of UL PRB capacity usage.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedUlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of measured samples of UL PRB capacity usage.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedUlSrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of Physical Resource Block (PRB) pairs used for Signaling Radio Bearers (SRB) in the uplink.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Accumulated sum of UL PRB capacity usage.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchCqiResLongUtilCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum utilization of CQI resources in the long resource pool.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchCqiResMediumUtilCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum utilization of CQI resources in the medium resource pool.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchCqiResShortUtilCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum utilization of CQI resources in the short resource pool.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchFailSr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of received Scheduling Requests (SR) over RACH due to a failure from the UE to access the node by means of SR over PUCCH.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received Scheduling Requests on PUCCH.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSrCqiResAllocAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Aggregated number of attempts to allocate PUCCH resources.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSrCqiResCongCqi
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times a PUCCH allocation request for CQI resource(s) could not be granted

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSrCqiResCongSr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times a PUCCH allocation request for SR resource(s) could not be granted.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSrMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Peak number of received Scheduling Requests on PUCCH during a TTI.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSrResLongUtilCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum utilization of SR resources in the long resource pool.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSrResMediumUtilCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum utilization of SR resources in the medium resource pool.

EntityDef.name: pmPucchSrResShortUtilCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Maximum utilization of SR resources in the short resource pool.

EntityDef.name: pmPwrBoostAttLowCovUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of power boost attempts for low-coverage UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmPwrBoostSuccLowCovUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful power boosts for low-coverage UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmRaAccHarqFailAfterContRes
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter counts the number of times a HARQ-process for random access message 4 fails for cases where the contention resolution counter has expired. The counter only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection setup or an RRC connection re-establishment message.

EntityDef.name: pmRaAccHarqFailWithinContRes
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter counts the number of times a HARQ-process for random access message 4 fails for cases where the contention resolution counter has not expired. The counter only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection setup or an RRC connection re-establishment message.

EntityDef.name: pmRaAllocCfra
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of allocated CFRA preambles.

EntityDef.name: pmRaAttCbra
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of detected contention-based random access preambles.

EntityDef.name: pmRaAttCfra
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of detected contention-free (explicitly signaled) random access preambles.

EntityDef.name: pmRaContResAndRrcRsp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Msg4 messages sent to the UE with Contention Resolution Identity and RRC Connection Response bundled.

EntityDef.name: pmRaContResOnly
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Msg4 messages sent to the UE with only Contention Resolution Identity MAC control element.

EntityDef.name: pmRaFailCbraMsg1DiscOoc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of CBRA preambles that are discarded because timing offset of CBRA preamble corresponds to a distance greater than configured cell range.

EntityDef.name: pmRaFailCbraMsg1DiscSched
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of CBRA preambles that are discarded because maximum number of RA Msg3 are already scheduled.

EntityDef.name: pmRaFailCbraMsg2Disc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of CBRA preambles for which no random access response (RA Msg2) was sent due to expiration of the random access response window.

EntityDef.name: pmRaFailCfraMsg1DiscOoc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of CFRA preambles that are discarded because timing offset of CFRA preamble corresponds to a distance greater than configured cell range.

EntityDef.name: pmRaFailCfraMsg1DiscSched
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of CFRA preambles that are discarded because maximum number of RA Msg3 are already scheduled.

EntityDef.name: pmRaFailCfraMsg2Disc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of CFRA preambles for which no random access response (RA Msg2) was sent due to expiration of the random access response window.

EntityDef.name: pmRaMsg2AttCbra
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of contention-based random access Msg2 attempts for each cell.

EntityDef.name: pmRaRejHarqFailAfterContRes
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter counts the number of times a HARQ-process for random access message 4 fails for cases where the contention resolution counter has expired. The counter only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and no RRC message or a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection reject or an RRC connection re-establishment reject message.

EntityDef.name: pmRaRejHarqFailWithinContRes
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter counts the number of times a HARQ-process for random access message 4 fails for cases where the contention resolution counter has not expired. The counter only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and no RRC message or a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection reject or an RRC connection re-establishment reject message.

EntityDef.name: pmRaSuccCbra
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successfully detected RA Msg3 for CBRA

EntityDef.name: pmRaSuccCfra
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successfully completed CFRA procedures. Measured when first UL-SCH message is received after detection of the CFRA preamble.

EntityDef.name: pmRaSuccSrInSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received Scheduling Requests on RACH from In-Synch UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmRaSuccSrOutOfSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of received Scheduling Request on RACH from Out-Of-Synch UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmRaSuccSrOutOfSyncPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of received SRs on RACH from Out-of-Sync PFT UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmRaUnassignedCfraFalse
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of detected Contention Free Random Access (CFRA, known as non-contention based random access in 3GPP term) preambles that are not allocated to any UE

EntityDef.name: pmRaUnassignedCfraSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unassigned Contention Free Random Access (CFRA, known as non-contention based random access in 3GPP term) preambles at each PRACH occasion during the reporting period.

EntityDef.name: pmRachNumContentionReport

EntityDef.name: pmRadioTbsPwrRestricted
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transport blocks on MAC level scheduled in UL where UE is considered to be power-limited. Transport blocks are excluded if scheduled for UEs with activated secondary carrier that is configured for UL transmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioTbsPwrUnrestricted
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transport blocks on MAC level scheduled in UL where UE is not considered to be power-limited. Transport blocks are excluded if scheduled for UEs with activated secondary carrier that is configured for UL transmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpResDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total amount of physical resources used for transmission in the downlink. Both successful and unsuccessful transmissions are counted.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpResUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total amount of physical resources used for transmission in the uplink. Both successful and unsuccessful transmissions are counted.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the downlink. This counter includes possible padding bits.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolDlSCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the downlink for secondary cell traffic (i.e. the UE has another cell as its primary component carrier (PCell)). This counter includes possible padding bits.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolDlSCellExt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total of assumed successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the DL for external SCell (ESCell) traffic as measured and reported on the ESCell.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolTxDlSCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total of successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the DL for SCell traffic as measured and reported on the PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolTxDlSCellExt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total of successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the DL for external SCell (ESCell) traffic as measured and reported on the PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total successfully transferred data volume on MAC-level in UL. This counter includes possible padding bits. Accumulates data traffic for UEs that use this cell as their PCell or SCell.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolUlSCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total of successfully received data volume on MAC-level in the UL for SCell traffic, that is, the UE has another cell as its PCell CC. This counter includes possible padding bits.

The average value of the reported sub-band 0 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqi2SubbandSamp. The counter is defined according to 32.425.

The average value of the reported sub-band 4 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqiSubbandSamp. The counter is defined according to 32.425.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioUeRepCqiSubband5Sum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The accumulated sum of all sub-band 5 CQI reported by UEs in the cell for rank 1 transmissions. The average value of the reported sub-band 5 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqiSubbandSamp. The counter is defined according to 32.425.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioUeRepCqiSubband6Sum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The accumulated sum of all sub-band 6 CQI reported by UEs in the cell for rank 1 transmissions. The average value of the reported sub-band 6 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqiSubbandSamp. The counter is defined according to 32.425.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioUeRepCqiSubband8Sum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The accumulated sum of all sub-band 8 CQI reported by UEs in the cell for rank 1 transmissions. The average value of the reported sub-band 8 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqiSubbandSamp. The counter is defined according to 32.425.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioUeRepCqiSubband9Sum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The accumulated sum of all sub-band 9 CQI reported by UEs in the cell for rank 1 transmissions. The average value of the reported sub-band 9 CQI within the measurement period can be obtained in conjunction with counter pmRadioUeRepCqiSubbandSamp. The counter is defined according to 32.425.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioUeRepCqiSubbandSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total sample count of rank 1 aperiodic CQI reported by UEs in the cell within the measurement period. It is used to compute the average CQI value for each sub-band. The counter is defined according to 32.425.

EntityDef.name: pmRateShapeTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The time where the UE have uplink data in a buffer and End-user bitrate shaping functionality will prohibit transmission in the uplink.

EntityDef.name: pmRlcArqDlAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of successful RLC PDU transmissions (ACKs) in the downlink direction.
When carrier aggregation is used, the total number of successful RLC PDU transmissions (ACKs) in the downlink direction is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmRlcArqDlNack
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of unsuccessful RLC PDU and RLC PDU segment transmissions (NACKs) in the downlink direction.
When carrier aggregation is used, the total number of unsuccessful RLC PDU and RLC PDU segment transmissions (NACKs) in the downlink direction is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).

EntityDef.name: pmRlcArqUlAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful RLC PDU transmissions (ACKs) in the uplink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmRlcArqUlNack
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful RLC PDU and RLC PDU segment transmissions (NACKs) in the uplink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmRlcDelayPktTransDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of samples for RLC delay measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmRlcDelayTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Aggregated time for the downlink160;RLC160;delay measure.

EntityDef.name: pmRlcPollRetxDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of sending downlink AM PDU retransmissions due to the poll retransmit timer expiry.

EntityDef.name: pmRlcPollRetxUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counter counts the number of receiving uplink AM PDU retransmissions due to the poll retransmit timer expiry.

EntityDef.name: pmRohcEstabFailCid

EntityDef.name: pmRohcEstabFailUeCap

EntityDef.name: pmSchedActivityCellDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The aggregated number of ms in which DRB data was required to be scheduled in the downlink. For CA it is counted on the PCell, regardless of which cell actually was used to send the SDU. Can be used as the PDCP timebase.

EntityDef.name: pmSchedActivityCellUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The aggregated number of ms in which DRB data was required to be scheduled in the uplink.

EntityDef.name: pmSchedActivityUeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total UEs scheduling activity in the downlink. For CA it is counted once on each cell the UE uses. Can be used as the MAC timebase.

EntityDef.name: pmSchedActivityUeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total UEs scheduling activity in the uplink.

EntityDef.name: pmSchedActivityUlTTI
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Scheduled Entities (SEs) in the uplink per cell, including TTI bundling grants and nonAdaptive re-transmissions. If divided with the number of TTIs, SE/TTI average can be obtained.

EntityDef.name: pmServiceTimeDrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of service seconds aggregated for DRBs in a cell. A DRB is said to be 180;in service180; from the first data on a DRB (UL or DL) until the last on the DRB is sent/received.

EntityDef.name: pmServiceTimeUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of service seconds aggregated for UEs in a cell. A UE is said to be 180;in service180; if any of its associated DRBs are.

EntityDef.name: pmSessionTimeDrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counters shows the accumulated active session time for all DRBs in a cell.

EntityDef.name: pmSessionTimeUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This counters shows the accumulated active session time for all UEs in a cell.

EntityDef.name: pmTtiBundlingDisable

EntityDef.name: pmTtiBundlingEnable

EntityDef.name: pmTtiBundlingUeMax

EntityDef.name: pmTtiBundlingUeSum

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtModAttCsfb

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Contexts Releases initiated by the RBS and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActCdt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE context releases by eNodeB due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically or by manual intervention) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: There is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActCdtAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE context releases by eNodeB due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically) or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: There is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActCdtAutoPnr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE context releases by eNodeB due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically) caused by a partial node restart or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: There is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context Releases initiated by the eNB due to handover execution failure and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActHoOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActHoOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is a PFT UE, it is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB, and the UE is in Out-of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB. The UE is a PFT UE, it is in Out-of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActPe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE context releases initiated by the RBS due to pre-emption and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActTnFail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNB due to S1 interface down, S1 bearer error indication, and SGW failure detection, and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActUeLost
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context releases by the RBS due that the radio connection with the UE is lost and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActUeLostOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActUeLostOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is a PFT UE, it is in Out-Of-Sync mode and has data in the buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbCdt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE context releases by eNodeB due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically or by manual intervention) or - automated UE recovery.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbCdtAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE context releases by eNodeB due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically) or - automated UE recovery.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbCdtAutoPnr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE context releases by eNodeB due to: - cell down time (initiated automatically) caused by a partial node restart or - automated UE recovery.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context Releases by the eNB due to handover execution failure.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbHoOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to handover failure. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Contexts Releases initiated by the RBS due to license reject.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB, and the UE is in Out-of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context Releases for each cell initiated by the eNodeB. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbPe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the RBS due to pre-emption. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbSir
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a UE context is released by eNodeB due to software initiated release. Occurs when a UE Context is identified as hanging.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbTuneOut
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Contexts Releases for Tune-out UEs initiated by the RBS. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbUeLost
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context releases by the eNB due to that the radio connection with the UE is lost.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbUeLostOos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbUeLostOosPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal UE Context releases initiated by the eNodeB due to lost radio connection with the UE. The UE is a PFT UE and it is in Out-Of-Sync mode.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of UE Context Releases by the MME with a cause regarded as abnormal.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalMmeAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of UE Context Releases initiated by the MME with a cause regarded as abnormal and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbCdma1xRtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to CDMA2000 1xRTT triggered by CS Fallback or soft lock of cell.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbCdma1xRttEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to CDMA2000 1xRTT triggered by CS Fallback Emergency

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbGsm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to GSM triggered either by CS Fallback or CS Fallback to WCDMA based on PSHO.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbGsmEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to GSM triggered either by CS Fallback Emergency or CS Fallback Emergency to WCDMA based on PSHO.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbHoPrepFail1xRtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a CS Fallback has been triggered where the UE should be doing a handover to a cell found by measurements, the handover preparation failed and the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbHoPrepFail1xRttEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a CS Fallback Emergency Call has been triggered where the UE should be doing a handover to a cell found by measurements, the handover preparation failed and the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbLimitedDualRadioUeCdma
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of RRC Connection Release triggered by CS Fallback for Limited Dual Radio UE LTE/1xRTT.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbMeasTO1xRtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a CS Fallback has been triggered where the UE should be doing a handover to a cell found by measurements, the measurement failed to find a target cell, and the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbMeasTO1xRttEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times a CS Fallback Emergency Call has been triggered where the UE should be doing a handover to a cell found by measurements, the measurement failed to find a target cell, and the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbTdScdma

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbTdScdmaEm

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbUlHoPrepTxTO1xRtt

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbUlHoPrepTxTO1xRttEm

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbWcdma

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelCsfbWcdmaEm

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelMmeAct

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelMmeHo
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of UE context releases by the MME during handover.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelNormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of normal UE Context Releases triggered by RBS. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelNormalEnbAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of normal UE Context Releases triggered by RBS and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelNormalEnbTuneOut

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCEUtraBestCellRsrq
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of RRC Connection Release with redirect to E-UTRA based on A3 Inter-frequency or A5 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRQ.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCEutraUlSinr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of RRC connection releases with redirect to E-UTRA, triggered when critical UL coverage reached. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCGsm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to GERAN.

EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to GERAN based on A2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSrvccMeasTO1xRtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times SRVCC to CDMA 1xRtt should have been triggered but the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRtt frequency using Release with Redirect. The counter is stepped if the B2 measurements failed to find a target cell and the target search timer timed out or B2 measurements were not possible.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRetainArpHigh
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that UE Context release is avoided. Occurs when a low ARP prioritized DRB is discovering an RLC DL Delivery Failure in a connection with high ARP prioritized DRB.

EntityDef.name: pmUeMeasAttCsfb1xRtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UE measurement attempts to find a CDMA2000 1xRTT target cell where CS Fallback call is triggered.

EntityDef.name: pmUeMeasAttCsfb1xRttEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UE measurement attempts to find a CDMA2000 1xRTT target cell where CS Fallback Emergency call is triggered.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The effective DL transport time comprises those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer. This counts for carrier aggregation and non-carrier aggregation UEs. Used for PDCP timebase.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The effective DL transport time, comprising those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer, is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpTimeDlCa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The effective DL transport time of carrier aggregation UE comprises those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer. This is used for PDCP timebase.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The effective DL transport time, comprising those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer, is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL volume transfer time used for UL UE Throughput. It comprises of time periods from when the 5th MAC SDU data reception of an UL buffer transfer on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpTimeUlCa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL volume transfer time used for UL carrier aggregation UE Throughput. Comprised of time periods from reception of 5th MAC SDU data in UL buffer transfer on Uu until buffer is empty. TTI emptying buffer is excluded.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL DRB volume used for UL UE Throughput. It comprises of the MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding the volume received in the first 4 data receptions of an UL buffer transfer and the TTI emptying the UL buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpVolUlCa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL DRB volume used for UL carrier aggregation UE throughput. Comprised of MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding volume received in first 4 data receptions of UL buffer transfer and TTI emptying UL buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsDetectedPuschNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration and confirmed by corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsDetectedPuschVolteNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants that are transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs with bearer mapped to QCI with VoIP service type. Reception must be confirmed by corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransNoAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of transmitted unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransPCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransPCellNoAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions. The grants are transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell, and that have no bearer mapped to a QCI with VoIP serviceType.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransVolte
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransVolteNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs that have bearer mapped to QCI with service type VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransVolteNoAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions. The grants are transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsWithDetectedPusch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants that are confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsWithDetectedPuschPCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsWithDetectedPuschVolte
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants that are transmitted to UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUnackedUeRelease
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of RRC Connection Releases that are sent by the eNodeB without expecting any acknowledgement.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityRbUlLowSampl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoLTE quality measurements that could not be used to determine the VoLTE quality of a VoLTE session (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) due to insufficient statistics. These measurements are excluded when the VoLTE integrity KPI is calculated.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityRbUlNok
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of unsatisfactory quality.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityRbUlOk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of satisfactory quality.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityUeUlLowSampl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoIP quality measurements that can not determine the VoIP satisfaction of a UE due to insufficient statistics. These measurements are excluded when the VoIP integrity KPI is calculated.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityUeUlNok
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of UE that are not satisfied with their VoIP quality.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityUeUlOk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of UE that are satisfied with their VoIP quality.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessAllowed
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with a decision to allow the UE to access WiFi.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessDecisionByWic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with decision information DECISION BY WIC.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessEval
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times eNodeB receives WiFi Access Decision Request message from the MME. MME requests decision to allow or reject UE in connected mode to access WiFi.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessEvalFailLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with decision information NO DECISION. This is because the feature for WiFi Mobility is not OPERABLE in the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessRej
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with a decision to reject the UE from accessing WiFi.
