EntityDef.name: pmAccessClassBarringCsfbDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The counter calculates the total time that feature Load-Based Access Barring has triggered Access Class Barring for Circuit Switched Fall Back (CSFB) in the cell.
PDF Ranges: [0]: ac-BarringFactor=p00 [1]: ac-BarringFactor=p05 [2]: ac-BarringFactor=p10 [3]: ac-BarringFactor=p15 [4]: ac-BarringFactor=p20 [5]: ac-BarringFactor=p25 [6]: ac-BarringFactor=p30 [7]: ac-BarringFactor=p40 [8]: ac-BarringFactor=p50 [9]: ac-BarringFactor=p60 [10]: ac-BarringFactor=p70 [11]: ac-BarringFactor=p75 [12]: ac-BarringFactor=p80 [13]: ac-BarringFactor=p85 [14]: ac-BarringFactor=p90 [15]: ac-BarringFactor=p95

EntityDef.name: pmAccessClassBarringModDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The counter calculates the total time that feature Load-Based Access Barring has triggered Access Class Barring for Mobile Originating (MO) Data in the cell.
PDF Ranges: [0]: ac-BarringFactor=p00 [1]: ac-BarringFactor=p05 [2]: ac-BarringFactor=p10 [3]: ac-BarringFactor=p15 [4]: ac-BarringFactor=p20 [5]: ac-BarringFactor=p25 [6]: ac-BarringFactor=p30 [7]: ac-BarringFactor=p40 [8]: ac-BarringFactor=p50 [9]: ac-BarringFactor=p60 [10]: ac-BarringFactor=p70 [11]: ac-BarringFactor=p75 [12]: ac-BarringFactor=p80 [13]: ac-BarringFactor=p85 [14]: ac-BarringFactor=p90 [15]: ac-BarringFactor=p95

EntityDef.name: pmAccessClassBarringMosDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The counter calculates the total time that feature Load-Based Access Barring has triggered Access Class Barring for Mobile Originating (MO) Signalling in the cell.
PDF Ranges: [0]: ac-BarringFactor=p00 [1]: ac-BarringFactor=p05 [2]: ac-BarringFactor=p10 [3]: ac-BarringFactor=p15 [4]: ac-BarringFactor=p20 [5]: ac-BarringFactor=p25 [6]: ac-BarringFactor=p30 [7]: ac-BarringFactor=p40 [8]: ac-BarringFactor=p50 [9]: ac-BarringFactor=p60 [10]: ac-BarringFactor=p70 [11]: ac-BarringFactor=p75 [12]: ac-BarringFactor=p80 [13]: ac-BarringFactor=p85 [14]: ac-BarringFactor=p90 [15]: ac-BarringFactor=p95

EntityDef.name: pmActiveDrbDlSumQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of number of DL active DRBs per QCI. A DL DRB is active if there are buffered DL data for the DRB. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP) Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlSectorCarrierDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The counter shows the distribution of DL UEs that are in 1 to N sectors.
[0]: Sum of active DL UEs that is connected to 1 sector [1]: Sum of active DL UEs that is connected to 2 sectors ----- [5]: Sum of active DL UEs that is connected to 6 sectors or more.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlSumQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of number of DL active UE per QCI. A DL active UE for a QCI is a UE that has buffered DL data for the QCI. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP) Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlSectorCarrierDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The counter shows the distribution of UL UEs that are in 1 to N sectors.
[0]: Sum of active UL UEs that is connected to 1 sector [1]: Sum of active UL UEs that is connected to 2 sectors ----- [5]: Sum of active UL UEs that is connected to 6 sectors or more.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlSumLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of number of UL active UE per LCG (Logical Channel Group). An UL active UE for a LCG is a UE that has buffered UL data for the LCG. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP)

EntityDef.name: pmAdjustAccessDynLoadCtrlDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Counter shows the distribution of the Cell Connection Intensity Control for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover). 100% means that the Cell Connection Intensity Control is not changed from its maximum value during the ROP period. The counter is only stepped when the optional feature Dynamic Load Control is activated.
PDF Ranges: [0]: [0..5[ % [1]: [5..10[ % [2]: [10..15[ % 8230; [19]: [95..100[ % [20]: 100 %

EntityDef.name: pmCaActDlIeNbSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of activated DL inter-eNodeB (IeNb) external SCells (ESCells) of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Inter-eNodeB carrier aggregation interactions can be through the IeNB-CA feature or the Elastic RAN feature.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have no activated ESCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated ESCell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated ESCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated ESCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated ESCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaActivatedDlFddTddSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of activated downlink SCells, identified by duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated FDD SCell. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated FDD SCells. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated FDD SCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated FDD SCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated TDD SCell. [5]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated TDD SCells. [6]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated TDD SCells. [7]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated TDD SCells. [8]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one FDD and one TDD SCells activated. [9]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one FDD and two TDD SCells activated. [10]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one FDD and three TDD SCells activated. [11]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two FDD and one TDD SCells activated. [12]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two FDD and two TDD SCells activated. [13]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three FDD and one TDD SCells activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCaActivatedDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of activated downlink SCells of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have no activated SCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated SCell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated SCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated SCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaAssignedCsSetsDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of channel selection resource sets (CS sets) assigned to UEs sharing this PCell within the HARQ bundling window. PDF: [0]: 1 set [1]: 2 sets 8230; [11]: 12 sets

EntityDef.name: pmCaAssignedPf3ResDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of PUCCH format3 resource sets assigned to UEs sharing this PCell within the HARQ bundling window.
PDF ranges: [0]: 1 set [1]: 2 sets 8230; [11]: 12 sets

EntityDef.name: pmCaCapableDlFddTddSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Downlink carrier aggregation capability reported by UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Only the maximum number of SCells, where at least one of the carriers is TDD, is considered.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus one TDD SCell. [1]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus two SCells, with at least one TDD SCell. [2]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus three SCells, with at least one TDD SCell. [3]: Number of UEs that are capable of FDD PCell plus four SCells, with at least one TDD SCell.

EntityDef.name: pmCaCapableDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of supported SCell CCs that support DL, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UEs that are not DL CA-capable at all, that is, PCell only. [1]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus one SCell. [2]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus two SCells. [3]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus three SCells. [4]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus four SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaCapableUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of supported SCell CCs, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UEs that are not UL CA-capable at all, that is, PCell only. [1]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus one SCell. [2]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus two SCells. [3]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus three SCells. [4]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus four SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredDlFddTddSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of configured downlink SCells identified by duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Only one bin is pegged for each UE and sample, based on all configured SCells when the counter is updated. For example, for a UE configured with one FDD and one TDD SCell, only bin 8 is incremented and not bin 0 or bin 4.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD SCell. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two FDD SCells. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three FDD SCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with four FDD SCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one TDD SCell. [5]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two TDD SCells. [6]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three TDD SCells. [7]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with four TDD SCells. [8]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD and one TDD SCell. [9]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD and two TDD SCells. [10]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one FDD and three TDD SCells. [11]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two FDD and one TDD SCell. [12]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two FDD and two TDD SCells. [13]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three FDD and one TDD SCell.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredDlIeNbSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
For inter-eNodeB (IeNb) carrier aggregation interactions, records the number of configured DL external SCells (ESCells) of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Inter-eNodeB carrier aggregation interactions can be through the IeNB-CA feature or the Elastic RAN feature.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are not configured with any ESCell. Includes CA capable UEs possibly configured with local SCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one ESCell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two ESCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three ESCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with four ESCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of configured DL SCell CCs, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.
PDF ranges: [0] Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are not configured with any SCell. [1]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with one SCell. [2]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with two SCells. [3]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with three SCells. [4]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with four SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaScheduledDlIeNbSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
For inter-eNodeB (IeNb) carrier aggregation interactions, records the mean number of UEs that have data scheduled on a DL external SCell (ESCell), counted by the number of component carriers hosted on external eNodeBs and simultaneously scheduled. UE is considered scheduled for carrier aggregation if the eNodeB has sent a PDCCH assignment indicating a PDSCH assignment. Inter-eNodeB carrier aggregation interactions can be through the IeNB-CA feature or the Elastic RAN feature.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have zero scheduled EScell. Includes scheduling only on PCell or SCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have one simultaneously scheduled EScell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have two simultaneously scheduled EScells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have three simultaneously scheduled EScells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have four simultaneously scheduled EScells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaScheduledDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of UEs that have data scheduled on DL, calculated by number of CCs scheduled simultaneously. UE is considered scheduled on a CC if a PDCCH assignment that indicates a PDSCH transmission on the CC is transmitted.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have one scheduled CC. [1]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have two CCs scheduled simultaneously. [2]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have three CCs scheduled simultaneously. [3]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have four CCs scheduled simultaneously. EntityDef.name: pmErabRelUlInactGapQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:

Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeOutAttQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of handover execution attempt for ERABs per QCI towards target cell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeOutSuccQci

The number of ERABs per QCI that was successfully handovered to the target cell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmInhibitImeisvFeature
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:

EntityDef.name: pmLaaActivatedSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of activated downlink LAA SCells, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have no activated LAA SCells [1]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have one activated LAA SCell [2]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have two activated LAA SCells [3]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have three activated LAA SCells [4]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have four activated LAA SCells

EntityDef.name: pmLaaCapableDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of supported LAA SCell CCs that support DL, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.

EntityDef.name: pmLaaConfigurableDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of configured DL LAA SCell CCs, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are not configured with any LAA SCell [1]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with one LAA SCell [2]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with two LAA SCells [3]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with three LAA SCells [4]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with four LAA SCells

EntityDef.name: pmLcgThpTimeUlLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL transmission time used for UL DRB Throughput per LCG. It comprises of time periods from when the 5th data transmission is received on Uu until the second last data transmission is received.

EntityDef.name: pmLcgThpVolUlLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL volume used for UL DRB Throughput per LCG. It comprises of the MAC SDU volume received on Uu per LCG, excluding the volume received in the first 4 data transmissions and the data transmission emptying the UL buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmMacDrbThpTimeDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC transfer time accumulated over all DRBs with a given QCI in the cell. Aggregates the number of ms in which MAC layer transmission in DL is needed for a DRB with that QCI. This includes buffer waiting times and possible HARQ retransmission delays. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. The DL MAC transfer time over all carriers is registered on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacDrbThpVolDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC SDU transmitted volume accumulated over all DRBs with a given QCI in the cell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlDrxSyncQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs with the corresponding QCI value.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlNoDrxNoSyncQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs with the corresponding QCI value.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlNoDrxSyncQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs with the corresponding QCI value.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC DRB latency time for each QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLcgThpVolUlLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Volume used for UL LCG throughput. Consists of the MAC SDU volume received for each LCG. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transmitted volume over all carriers is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlDrxSyncSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state and are included into the DL MAC DRB latency measurements for each QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlNoDrxNoSyncSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state and are included into the DL MAC DRB latency measurements for each QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlNoDrxSyncSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state and are included into the DL MAC DRB latency measurements for each QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of data bursts used for the DL MAC DRB transfer time and latency measurements for each QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMaxDeltaSinrDlComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of the estimated SINR gain caused by interference from neighboring cells within the Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point cluster.
PDF ranges: [0]: =< 1.0 [1]: ]1.0..2.0] [2]: ]2.0..3.0] ... [7]: ]7.0..8.0] [8]: ]8.0..9.0] [9]: ]9.0..10] [10]: ]10.0..15.0] [11]: ]15.0..20] [12]: > 20.0

EntityDef.name: pmModImeisvParamSet
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of times IMEISV of UE causes the application of specific parameter settings for a certain function.
PDF ranges: [0]: Specific parameter setting 1, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. [1]: Specific parameter setting 2, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. ... [19]: Specific parameter setting 20, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceAggregationDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
This counter indicates the distribution of the Physical Downlink Control Channel (PDCCH) Control Channel Element (CCE) aggregation levels selected during the PDCCH allocation phase.
Ranges: [0]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 1 [1]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 2 [2]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 4 [3]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 8

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceUsedDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of CCEs used for DL grants per QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceUsedUlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of CCEs used for UL grants. All CCEs used for UL grants for a specific UE will be counted on the configured QCI that has the highest priority. This is since the UL grant does not contain any information about what the grant will be used for by the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
PDF of % of CCEs utilized compared with total CCEs available (at the maximum CFI permitted by pdcchCfiMode) each subframe, considering bandwidth and antenna configuration. [0]: utilization <= 5% [1]: 5% < utilization <= 10% [2]: 10% < utilization <= 15% [3]: 15% < utilization <= 20% [4]: 20% < utilization <= 25% [5]: 25% < utilization <= 30% [6]: 30% < utilization <= 35% [7]: 35% < utilization <= 40% [8]: 40% < utilization <= 45% [9]: 45% < utilization <= 50% [10]: 50% < utilization <= 55% [11]: 55% < utilization <= 60% [12]: 60% < utilization <= 65% [13]: 65% < utilization <= 70% [14]: 70% < utilization <= 75% [15]: 75% < utilization <= 80% [16]: 80% < utilization <= 85% [17]: 85% < utilization <= 90% [18]: 90% < utilization <= 95% [19]: 95% < utilization <= 100%
In subframes where the number of available CCEs is zero, the lowest bin is incremented.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCfiUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: PDF of number of subframes each CFI value was assigned [0]: CFI = 1 [1]: CFI = 2 [2]: CFI = 3

EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
This counter counts the Physical Downlink Control Channel (PDCCH) symbol 0 power utilization for PDCCHs transmitted on the air interface. It counts the PDCCH power % utilized in OFDM symbol 0, compared to the total available PDCCH power in the same symbol, while considering bandwidth and antenna configuration.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchSym1PwrUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
This counter counts the Physical Downlink Control Channel (PDCCH) symbol 1 power utilization for PDCCHs transmitted on the air interface. It counts the PDCCH power % utilized in OFDM symbol 1, compared to the total available PDCCH power in the same symbol, while considering bandwidth and antenna configuration.
Ranges: [0]: utilization <= 10% [1]: 10% < utilization <= 20% [2]: 20% < utilization <= 30% [3]: 30% < utilization <= 40% [4]: 40% < utilization <= 50% [5]: 50% < utilization <= 60% [6]: 60% < utilization <= 70% [7]: 70% < utilization <= 80% [8]: 80% < utilization <= 90% [9]: 90% < utilization <= 100%

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchSym2PwrUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
This counter counts the Physical Downlink Control Channel (PDCCH) symbol 2 power utilization for PDCCHs transmitted on the air interface. It counts the PDCCH power % utilized in OFDM symbol 2, compared to the total available PDCCH power in the same symbol, while considering bandwidth and antenna configuration.
Ranges: [0]: utilization <= 10% [1]: 10% < utilization <= 20% [2]: 20% < utilization <= 30% [3]: 30% < utilization <= 40% [4]: 40% < utilization <= 50% [5]: 50% < utilization <= 60% [6]: 60% < utilization <= 70% [7]: 70% < utilization <= 80% [8]: 80% < utilization <= 90% [9]: 90% < utilization <= 100%

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchSym3PwrUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
This counter counts the Physical Downlink Control Channel (PDCCH) symbol 3 power utilization for PDCCHs transmitted on the air interface. It counts the PDCCH power % utilized in OFDM symbol 3, compared to the total available PDCCH power in the same symbol, while considering bandwidth and antenna configuration. Note that this counter can only be used by 1.4 MHz systems.
Ranges: [0]: utilization <= 10% [1]: 10% < utilization <= 20% [2]: 20% < utilization <= 30% [3]: 30% < utilization <= 40% [4]: 40% < utilization <= 50% [5]: 50% < utilization <= 60% [6]: 60% < utilization <= 70% [7]: 70% < utilization <= 80% [8]: 80% < utilization <= 90% [9]: 90% < utilization <= 100%

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpInactSecDlVolteDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of the number of times there has been greater than 1 second without receiving an SDU at the DL PDCP layer on a QCI1 DRB.
PDF ranges: [0]: [1..2[ s [1]: [2..3[ s [2]: [3..4[ s [3]: [4..5[ s [4]: [5..6[ s [5]: [6..7[ s [6]: [7..8[ s [7]: [8..9[ s [8]: [9..10[ s [9]: >=10 s

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpInactSecUlVolteDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of the number of times there has been greater than 1 second without receiving an SDU at the UL PDCP layer on a QCI1 DRB.
PDF ranges: [0]: [1..2[ s [1]: [2..3[ s [2]: [3..4[ s [3]: [4..5[ s [4]: [5..6[ s [5]: [6..7[ s [6]: [7..8[ s [7]: [8..9[ s [8]: [9..10[ s [9]: >=10 s

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatPktTransDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of samples for DL Latency measurements during measurement period per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpLatTimeDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Aggregated DL Latency for a measurement period per QCI. When carrier aggregation is used, the DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on the UE's primary component carrier (PCell).
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlAqmQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI discarded due to Active Queue Management (AQM).
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI discarded due to AQM is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlHoQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to HO per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded due to HO per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlPelrQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI that are discarded in the PDCP layer due to reasons other than handover or active queue management. No part of these packets has been transmitted over the air.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI discarded due to reasons other than handover or active queue management is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlPelrUuQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air but not positively acknowledged due to reasons other than handover, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) per QCI for which at least a part has been transmitted over the air but not positively acknowledged due to reasons other than handover, and it was decided that no more transmission attempts will be done, is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktLostUlMissingPdus2Qci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of lost packets in UL due to missing PDUs differentiated per QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktLostUlMissingPdusQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of lost packets in UL due to any of the following causes, differentiated per QCI. Causes are either RLC re-assembly failure, HARQ failure or UE PDCP discarded packets due to outdated PDUs.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktLostUlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of UL packets (PDCP SDUs) lost per QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktLostUlRohcFail2Qci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of lost packets in UL due to RoHC decompression failures, differentiated per QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktLostUlRohcFailQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of lost packets in UL due to RoHC decompression failures, differentiated per QCI.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktReceivedDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) received in PDCP in the RBS per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) received in PDCP in the RBS per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktReceivedUlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of UL packets (PDCP SDUs) received per QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktTransDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) transmitted successfully per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total number of DL packets (PDCP SDUs) transmitted successfully per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlCmpHdrQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume of compressed PDCP SDU headers that has been transmitted from the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume of compressed PDCP SDU headers that has been transmitted from the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbLastTTIQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total DL PDCP SDU volume per QCI that is transmitted in the last TTI when the buffer for a DRB that maps to the given QCI is emptied.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total DL PDCP SDU volume per QCI that is transmitted in the last TTI when the buffer for a DRB that maps to the given QCI is emptied is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been transferred (UM and AM) on Data Radio Bearers in the downlink direction per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been transferred (UM and AM) on Data Radio Bearers in the downlink direction per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlDrbTransQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume (PDCP SDU) on Data Radio Bearers that has been transmitted in the downlink direction in the PDCP layer per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolDlHdrQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume of uncompressed PDCP SDU headers that has been received in the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The total volume of uncompressed PDCP SDU headers that has been received in the Robust Header Compression entity in the downlink direction per QCI is measured on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlCmpHdrQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume of compressed PDCP SDU headers that has been received in the Robust Header Compression entity in the uplink direction per QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlDrbQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been received on Data Radio Bearers in the uplink direction per QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpVolUlHdrQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total volume of decompressed PDCP SDU headers that has been transmitted from the Robust Header Compression entity in the uplink direction per QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlDtchFirstTransQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of PRB pairs used in DL per QCI for HARQ initial transmissions.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedDlDtchVirtualCellsDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of PRB pairs simultaneously utilized for DL by different UEs in different sectors of a combined cell as a result of virtual cells.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of PRB pairs only used for one UE within a combined cell. [1]: Number of PRB pairs used simultaneously in 2 sectors of a combined cell for different UEs as a result of virtual cells. [2]: Number of PRB pairs used simultaneously in 3 sectors of a combined cell for different UEs as a result of virtual cells. [3]: Number of PRB pairs used simultaneously in 4 sectors of a combined cell for different UEs as a result of virtual cells. [4]: Number of PRB pairs used simultaneously in 5 sectors of a combined cell for different UEs as a result of virtual cells. [5]: Number of PRB pairs used simultaneously in 6 sectors of a combined cell for different UEs as a result of virtual cells. [6]: Number of PRB pairs used simultaneously in 7 sectors of a combined cell for different UEs as a result of virtual cells. [7]: Number of PRB pairs used simultaneously in 8 or more sectors of a combined cell for different UEs as a result of virtual cells.

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUsedUlDtchQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of PRB pairs used in UL per QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUtilDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
A distribution that shows the downlink Physical Resource Block (PRB) pair utilization (total number of used PRB pairs by available PRB pairs) on the Physical Downlink Shared Channel (PDSCH).
PDF ranges: [0]: 0 % <= Utilization < 10 % [1]: 10 % <= Utilization < 20 % [2]: 20 % <= Utilization < 30 % [3]: 30 % <= Utilization < 40 % [4]: 40 % <= Utilization < 50 % [5]: 50 % <= Utilization < 60 % [6]: 60 % <= Utilization < 70 % [7]: 70 % <= Utilization < 80 % [8]: 80 % <= Utilization < 90 % [9]: 90 % <= Utilization

EntityDef.name: pmPrbUtilUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
A distribution that shows the uplink Physical Resource Block (PRB) pair utilization (total number of used PRB pairs by available PRB pairs) on the Physical Uplink Shared Channel (PUSCH).
PDF ranges: [0]: 0 % <= Utilization < 10 % [1]: 10 % <= Utilization < 20 % [2]: 20 % <= Utilization < 30 % [3]: 30 % <= Utilization < 40 % [4]: 40 % <= Utilization < 50 % [5]: 50 % <= Utilization < 60 % [6]: 60 % <= Utilization < 70 % [7]: 70 % <= Utilization < 80 % [8]: 80 % <= Utilization < 90 % [9]: 90 % <= Utilization

EntityDef.name: pmRaAttCbraBr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of CE (Coverage enhancement) level of detected contention-based random access preambles from BR (Bandwidth reduced) low complexity UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1

EntityDef.name: pmRaAttTaDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of measured TA values from all detected possible random access attempts. TA values are expressed as a percentage of TA that correspond to configured cell range.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..9]% [1]: [10..19]% [2]: [20..29]% [3]: [30..39]% [4]: [40..49]% [5]: [50..59]% [6]: [60..69]% [7]: [70..79]% [8]: [80..89]% [9]: [90..99]% [10]: [100..109]% [11]: [110..200]%

EntityDef.name: pmRaBackoffDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Backoff parameter BI value used in RARs (RaMsg2) or BI estimates when the feature Dynamic RA Backoff Indicator is disabled. The BI is included in RARs only when the feature is enabled. BI is calculated independently of the feature state. The corresponding pmRaBackoffDistr bins are incremented.
Time ranges for BI (and BI estimate) below indicate the time that the UEs re-attempt RA within, specified by 3GPP TS 36.321.
PDF ranges: [0]: BI = 0 0 ms [1]: BI = 1 [0..10] ms [2]: BI = 2 [0..20] ms [3]: BI = 3 [0..30] ms [4]: BI = 4 [0..40] ms [5]: BI = 5 [0..60] ms [6]: BI = 6 [0..80] ms [7]: BI = 7 [0..120] ms [8]: BI = 8 [0..160] ms [9]: BI = 9 [0..240] ms [10] BI = 10 [0..320] ms [11]: BI = 11 [0..480] ms [12]: BI = 12 [0..960] ms

EntityDef.name: pmRaContResAccDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of the delay between reception of random access message 3 and successful transmission of random access message 4. The counter only counts message 4s that contain a contention resolution identity and an RRC connection setup or an RRC connection re-establishment message.
PDF ranges: [0]: =< 8 ms, [1]: ]8..16] ms, [2]: ]16..24] ms, [3]: ]24..32] ms, [4]: ]32..40] ms, [5]: ]40..48] ms, [6]: ]48..56] ms, [7]: ]56..64] ms, [8]: > 64 ms

EntityDef.name: pmRaFailCbraMsg2DiscBr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of CE (Coverage enhancement) level of CBRA preambles from BR (Bandwidth reduced) low complexity UEs for which no random access response (random access Msg2) was sent due to expiration of the random access response window.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1

EntityDef.name: pmRaMsg2AttCbraBr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of CE (Coverage enhancement) level of contention-based random access Msg2 attempts from BR (Bandwidth reduced) low complexity UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: CE level 0 [1]: CE level 1

EntityDef.name: pmRaMsg3DtxCbraTxDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of contention-based random access Msg3 scheduled in UL determined as DTX, distributed whether they are first, second, third transmission, and so on.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of first transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX. [1]: Number of second transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX. [2]: Number of third transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX. [3]: Number of fourth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX. [4]: Number of fifth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX. [5]: Number of sixth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX. [6]: Number of seventh transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX. [7]: Number of eighth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 determined as DTX.

EntityDef.name: pmRaMsg3NackCbraTxDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of contention-based random access Msg3 scheduled in UL which resulted in NACK, or CRC fail. These are distributed whether they are the first, second, third transmissions, and so on.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of first transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK. [1]: Number of second transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK. [2]: Number of third transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK. [3]: Number of fourth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK. [4]: Number of fifth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK. [5]: Number of sixth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK. [6]: Number of seventh transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK. [7]: Number of eighth transmission attempts of contention-based random access Msg3 that resulted in NACK.

EntityDef.name: pmRaRrcRspDistr

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal E-RAB releases by MME.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMmeAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by MME. Counter is stepped if data was lost in either UL or DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMmeActGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME within this cell. Counter is stepped if data was present in UL or DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMmeGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by MME excluding successful handover. Counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelMmeGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME excluding successful handover within this cell. Counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelNormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of normal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by eNB.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelNormalEnbGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of normal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by RBS within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexLcgThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL transmission time used for UL DRB Throughput. It is comprised of time periods from when the 5th data transmission is received on Uu until the second last data transmission is received.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI and ARP are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexLcgThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL volume used for UL DRB Throughput. It is comprised of MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding volume received in the first 4 data transmissions and data transmission emptying UL buffer.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI and ARP are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC DRB latency time.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDlDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDlNoDrxNoSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDlNoDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlDrxSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state and are included into DL MAC DRB latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlNoDrxNoSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state and are included into DL MAC DRB latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlNoDrxSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state and are included into DL MAC DRB latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts used for DL MAC DRB transfer time and latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpLatPktTransDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets for DL Latency measurements.
When CA is used, DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpLatTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Aggregated DL Latency for measurement period. Effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering buffer until the first data has been transmitted to UE.
When CA is used, DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpVolDlDrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been transferred (UM and AM) on DRBs in DL.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total volume is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpVolDlDrbLastTTI
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total DL PDCP SDU volume that is transmitted in the last TTI when buffer for DRB is emptied.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total DL PDCP SDU volume is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpVolDlDrbLastTTIUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total DL PDCP SDU volume to UE level that is transmitted in the last TTI when buffer for DRB is emptied.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total DL PDCP SDU volume is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexUeThpTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Effective DL transport time comprising those periods from when the first part of PDCP SDU of DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until buffer is emptied, excluding TTI emptying buffer.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Effective DL transport time is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexUeThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL volume transfer time used for UL UE Throughput. It is comprised of time periods from when the 5th MAC SDU data reception of UL buffer transfer on Uu until buffer is emptied, excluding TTI emptying buffer.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexUeThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL DRB volume used for UL UE Throughput. It is comprised of MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding volume received in the first 4 data receptions of UL buffer transfer and TTI emptying UL buffer.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmAtoMeasRepUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs that report the related EUTRAN cell as the strongest cell in connection with measurements initiated for Admission-Triggered Offload.

EntityDef.name: pmAtoQualifiedUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received UE measurement reports in connection with Admission-Triggered Offload that fulfill both RSRP and RSRQ requirements. This is a subcounter of pmAtoMeasRepUe.160;

EntityDef.name: pmCaRedirectMeasRepUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs that report the related EUTRAN cell as the strongest cell in connection with CA-triggered redirection, when feature CA-Aware IFLB is used.

EntityDef.name: pmCaRedirectQualifiedUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of received UE measurement reports that fulfill both RSRP and RSRQ requirements in connection with CA-triggered redirection, when feature CA-Aware IFLB is used.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeAttLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeAttLteInterFLb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts due to load balancing.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeAttLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeAttLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeAttLteIntraFTuneOut
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts made by Tune-out UEs

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeAttLteSpifho
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempted inter-frequency handover executions towards the related cell, due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeAttNonMob
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE handover executions towards the related cell due to non-mobility.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeOutAttLteInterFQci1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of out-going intra-LTE, inter-frequency handover execution attempts for QCI1 ERAB.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeOutSuccLteInterFQci1
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful out-going intra LTE inter frequency handover execution for QCI1 ERAB.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccLteInterFLb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers that was performed for load balancing reasons.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers that was performed due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccLteInterFRedirectCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - triggered by handover preparation failure from target CSG or Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handovers.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccLteIntraFTuneOut
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE intra frequency handovers made by Tune-out UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccLteSpifho
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter-frequency handovers that were performed due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeSuccNonMob
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE handovers that were performed due to non-mobility reasons.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExecAttLteInterFCaRedirect
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of attempted inter-frequency handover executions towards the related cell, due to CA Triggered Redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.

EntityDef.name: pmHoExecSuccLteInterFCaRedirect
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of successful inter-frequency handover executions towards the related cell, attempted due to CA Triggered Redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.

EntityDef.name: pmHoOscInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counter pmHoOscInterF counts every inter-frequency HO that is considered to be an oscillating HO. pmHoOscInterF is incremented when handover preparation is attempted.

EntityDef.name: pmHoOscIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counter pmHoOscIntraF counts every intra-frequency HO that is considered to be an oscillating HO. pmHoOscIntraF is incremented when handover preparation is attempted.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteInterFCaRedirect
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of attempted inter-frequency handover preparations towards the related cell, due to CA triggered redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteInterFLb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation due to load balancing.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteInterFRedirectCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency, - triggered by handover preparation failure from target CSG or Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempts to start outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparation, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start intra LTE intra frequency handover preparation.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttLteSpifho
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter-frequency handover preparation due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepAttNonMob
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE handover preparation due to non-mobility reasons.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteInterFCaRedirect
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of successful inter-frequency handover preparations towards the related cell, attempted due to CA Triggered Redirection performed during Initial UE connection setup, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteInterFLb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations that was performed for load balancing reasons.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations that was performed due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteInterFRedirectCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - triggered by handover preparation failure from target CSG or Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparations, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handover preparations.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccLteSpifho
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter-frequency handover preparations due to feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover.

EntityDef.name: pmHoPrepSuccNonMob
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE handover preparations due to non-mobility reasons.

EntityDef.name: pmHoTooEarlyHoInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of too early HO on an inter frequency relation.

EntityDef.name: pmHoTooEarlyHoIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of too early HO on an intra frequency relation.

EntityDef.name: pmHoTooLateHoInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of too late HO on an inter frequency relation.

EntityDef.name: pmHoTooLateHoIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of too late HO on an intra frequency relation.

EntityDef.name: pmHoWrongCellInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an inter frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is the attempted target cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoWrongCellIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an intra frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is the attempted target cell.

EntityDef.name: pmHoWrongCellReestInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an inter frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is where the UE reestablished connection after the failed HO.

EntityDef.name: pmHoWrongCellReestIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts every detected event of HO to the wrong cell on an intra frequency relation, when this neighbor cell is where the UE reestablished connection after the failed HO.

EntityDef.name: pmLbMeasRepUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs that report the related EUTRAN cell as the strongest cell in connection with measurements initiated for load balancing or offload.

EntityDef.name: pmLbQualifiedUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of received UE measurement reports that fulfill both RSRP and RSRQ requirements. This is a subcounter of pmLbMeasRepUe.

EntityDef.name: pmLbTpAcceptedUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs that are accepted for throughput based load balancing.

EntityDef.name: pmLbTpEvalUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of throughput evaluations of UEs that are candidates for throughput based load balancing.

EntityDef.name: pmLbTpUlAcceptedUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs that are accepted for throughput based load balancing and accepted in UL evaluation.

EntityDef.name: pmSpifhoReportedUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of UEs that report the related LTE cell as the cell with the best RSRP value in connection with measurements initiated by Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover. Used to calculate the SPIFHO measurement success rate for the related cell.

EntityDef.name: pmAtoMeasuredUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records number of UEs selected for measurements that qualify for Admission-Triggered Offload (ATO) towards cells on the related LTE frequency. Used to calculate the ATO measurement success rate for related cells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaRedirectMeasuredUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of UEs selected for measurements that qualify for CA triggered redirection towards cells on the related frequency, when the feature CA-aware IFLB is used. Used to calculate the LB measurement success rate for the related cells.

EntityDef.name: pmLbMeasuredUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Records the number of UEs selected for measurements that qualify for load balancing action towards cells on the related frequency. Used to calculate the LB measurement success rate for the related cells.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsInterestIndication
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received RRC MBMS INTEREST INDICATION messages that indicate a MBMS frequency different to the cell's frequency.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsInterestIndicationNonServ
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received RRC MBMS INTEREST INDICATION messages that result in UE setup so it can receive eMBMS on a non-serving cell frequency.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsInterestIndicationPCell

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsInterestIndicationSCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received RRC MBMS INTEREST INDICATION messages that result in UE setup so it can receive eMBMS on an SCell frequency.

EntityDef.name: pmSpifhoMeasuredUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of UEs selected for measurements that qualify for feature Service or Priority-Triggered Inter-frequency Handover action towards cells on the related frequency. Used to calculate the SPIFHO measurement success rate for the related cells.

EntityDef.name: pmA3InterFBestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A3 inter-frequency measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmA3InterFBestCellEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A3 inter-frequency measurement reports with trigger quantity RSRP received.

EntityDef.name: pmA3InterFBestCellEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received A3 inter-frequency measurement reports for target cell measurements triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmA5BestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A5 measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmA5BestCellEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A5 measurement reports received with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmA5BestCellEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received A5 inter-frequency measurement reports for target cell measurements triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmAccessClassBarringEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter calculates the total time that feature Load-Based Access Barring has triggered Access Class Barring for Emergency calls in the cell.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveDrbDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of the contributions from each UE in the cell of the number of active DRBs in the downlink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveDrbUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of the contributions from each UE in the cell of the number of active DRBs in the uplink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Peak number of UEs considered active in the downlink direction, i.e. has designated data in UE dedicated buffer in the eNB. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs considered active in the downlink direction. For a carrier aggregation UE, is counted on Pcell.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDrbSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of active UE or active DRB measurement samples. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP)

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlMax
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Peak number of UEs considered active in the uplink direction, i.e. the UE is considered to have data in its buffer. The value is a maximum of a set of samples, where each sample is an average of active UEs per ms (throughout the frame), during a sample period shorter than the ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UEs considered active in the uplink direction.

EntityDef.name: pmAdjustAccessDynLoadCtrl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter shows how long time within the ROP period that the cell load control window for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover) has been down regulated from its maximum value due to high procedure latency and/or high drop rate.

EntityDef.name: pmAdjustAccessMpLoadCtrl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter shows how long time within the ROP period that the DU or Baseband load control window for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover) has been down regulated from its maximum value due to high MP load.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrCandNrelCgiAdd
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of automatic neighbour relation candidates added by CGI report.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrCandNrelRem
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of automatic neighbour relation candidates removed.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrCandNrelX2Add
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of automatic neighbour relation candidates added by X2 procedure.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrHoSuccLevelLow
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of cell relations where the EUtranCellRelation::hoSuccLevel has changed from MEDIUM to LOW.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrHoSuccLevelMedium
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of cell relations where the EUtranCellRelation::hoSuccLevel has changed from HIGH to MEDIUM.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrNeighbrelAdd
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of neighbour relations added by the ANR function.

EntityDef.name: pmAnrNeighbrelRem
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of neighbour relations removed by the ANR function.

EntityDef.name: pmB2BestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total B2 measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmB2BestCellEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total B2 measurement reports received with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmB2BestCellEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received B2 measurement reports for target cell measurements triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of traffic Bad Coverage measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovOutSearchEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 measurement reports received because outer search zone is entered. Used when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is active.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovOutSearchEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 measurement reports received because outer search zone is entered with trigger quantity RSRP. Used when feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is active.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovSearchEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of A2 measurement reports received due to entering the Search zone. This counter is used when the feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovSearchEvalReportRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 measurement reports received because the search zone is entered with trigger quantity RSRP. This counter is used when the feature Mobility Control at Poor Coverage is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBadCovSearchEvalReportUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total A2 event reports because the search zone threshold is entered with trigger quantity UL SINR. Counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmBbUeMeasAllocAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to allocate an object from the internal memory pool dedicated to UE throughput measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmBbUeMeasAllocSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful object allocations from the internal memory pool dedicated to UE throughput measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmBestCellEvalReport
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of traffic Best Cell measurement reports received.

EntityDef.name: pmCaCapableDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of carrier aggregation capable UE measurement samples.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of carrier aggregation configured UE measurement samples.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredMeasAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempted SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done based on coverage measurements. This includes changes of cells due to receiving an A6 report.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredMeasSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful SCell configurations, excluding RRC signaling to UE, when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done based on coverage measurements. This includes changes of cells due to receiving an A6 report.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredNoMeasAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempted SCell configurations when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done without using any coverage measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredNoMeasSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful SCell configurations, excluding RRC signaling to UE, when selection of the cell to use as SCell is done without using any coverage measurements.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of 5-second samples of SCell configuration accumulations included in ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfigured
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of SCell deconfigurations, except when the same cell is deconfigured and configured as SCell in the same RRC message. Has subcounters for specific reasons for SCell deconfiguration.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfiguredLostCoverage
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Subcounter to pmCaDeconfigured. The number of SCell deconfigurations due to poor coverage in the SCell.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfiguredSCellChange
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Subcounter to pmCaDeconfigured. The number of SCell deconfigurations due to changing to another SCell.

EntityDef.name: pmCaDeconfiguredSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of 5-second samples of SCell deconfiguration accumulations included in ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmCellAdmControlPdcchRej
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counter is stepped whenever we have a reject due to that pdcch is limiting new connections.

EntityDef.name: pmCellAdmControlPdcchRejMeas
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counter is stepped whenever we would have had a reject due to that pdcch is limiting new connections.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownLockAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled).

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownLockMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownUnlockMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been enabled.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDowntimeAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Length of time the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled). The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDowntimeMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Length of time the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily. The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover executions that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover executions that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover execution attempts due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFUeMeas
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of outgoing intra-LTE, inter-frequency handover execution attempts based on A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement report.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFUeMeasRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of outgoing intra-LTE, inter-frequency handover execution attempts based on A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempts to start outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency HO execution, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraFAfterResync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of intra-LTE intra-frequency handover execution attempts after resync has been performed.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover executions that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeAttLteIntraFTuneOut
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of intra LTE intra frequency handover execution attempts made by Tune-out UEs

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handovers that was performed due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFUeMeas
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing intra-LTE, inter-frequency handovers execution based on A3 Inter-frequency or A5 measurement report.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteInterFUeMeasRsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing, intra-LTE, inter-frequency handovers execution based on A3 inter-frequency or A5 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handovers.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFAfterResync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful intra-LTE intra-frequency handovers after resync has been performed.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handovers that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoExeSuccLteIntraFTuneOut
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE intra frequency handovers made by Tune-out UEs.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLowCovUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of handover preparation attempts to start outgoing intra LTE HO for low-coverage UE.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparation due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempts to start outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparation, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of attempts to start intra LTE intra frequency handover preparation.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency, - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepAttLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of attempted handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency, - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLowCovUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful HO preparations for outgoing intra LTE HO for low-coverage UE.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - inter-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFMbms
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful outgoing intra LTE inter frequency handover preparations that was performed due to MBMS Interest.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteInterFUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful outgoing intra-LTE inter-frequency handover preparations, triggered by bad UL quality in the source cell. Used when feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteIntraF
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of successful intra LTE intra frequency handover preparations.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteIntraFCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to closed access mode CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellHoPrepSuccLteIntraFHybridCsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of successful handover preparations that are: - outgoing intra-LTE, - intra-frequency and - to Hybrid CSG cell.

EntityDef.name: pmCellSleepTime
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Time the cell has been disabled due to energy saving mode. The system sets cell MO OperationalState to Disabled and AvailabilityStatus to Off_duty. The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmConfigRejDlComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of measurement requests for Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point triggered by Layer 2 and rejected by Layer 3.

EntityDef.name: pmConfirmedUeRelReqPft
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times an RRC connection is released to IDLE, after a FAPPI message is received with DC field set to 0 from a PFT UE.

EntityDef.name: pmContDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the downlink direction due to lack of eNodeB resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContDlCapLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the downlink direction due to lack of DL capacity license.

EntityDef.name: pmContDlHw
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The counter aggregates the number of ms for which contention has occurred in the downlink direction due to lack of hardware resources.

EntityDef.name: pmContDlPdcch
