EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to GERAN based on B2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCGsmB2Rsrq
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to GERAN based on B2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRQ.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCGsmUlSinr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of RRC connection releases with redirect to GSM, triggered when critical UL coverage reached. This counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCTdScdma
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRA TDD

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCUtraUlSinr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of RRC connection releases with redirect to UTRA, triggered when critical UL coverage reached. This counter is used when the feature Uplink-Triggered Inter-Frequency Mobility is activated.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCUtranA2Rsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRAN based on A2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCUtranA2Rsrq
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRAN based on A2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRQ.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCUtranB2Rsrp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRAN based on B2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRP.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCUtranB2Rsrq
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRAN based on B2 measurement report with trigger quantity RSRQ.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSCWcdma
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of Session Continuity RRC Connection Release with redirect to UTRA FDD.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelSrvccA2Critical1xRtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the A2 critical report was received from the UE and the UE was redirected to a CDMA2000 1xRtt frequency using Release with Redirect.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRetainArpHigh
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that UE Context release is avoided. Occurs when a low ARP prioritized DRB is discovering an RLC DL Delivery Failure in a connection with high ARP prioritized DRB.

EntityDef.name: pmUeMeasAttCsfb1xRtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UE measurement attempts to find a CDMA2000 1xRTT target cell where CS Fallback call is triggered.

EntityDef.name: pmUeMeasAttCsfb1xRttEm
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of UE measurement attempts to find a CDMA2000 1xRTT target cell where CS Fallback Emergency call is triggered.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpTimeDlCa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The effective DL transport time of carrier aggregation UE comprises those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer. This is used for PDCP timebase.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). The effective DL transport time, comprising those periods from when the first part of the PDCP SDU of the DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer, is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL volume transfer time used for UL UE Throughput. It comprises of time periods from when the 5th MAC SDU data reception of an UL buffer transfer on Uu until the buffer is emptied, excluding the TTI emptying the buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpTimeUlCa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL volume transfer time used for UL carrier aggregation UE Throughput. Comprised of time periods from reception of 5th MAC SDU data in UL buffer transfer on Uu until buffer is empty. TTI emptying buffer is excluded.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL DRB volume used for UL UE Throughput. It comprises of the MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding the volume received in the first 4 data receptions of an UL buffer transfer and the TTI emptying the UL buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmUeThpVolUlCa
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL DRB volume used for UL carrier aggregation UE throughput. Comprised of MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding volume received in first 4 data receptions of UL buffer transfer and TTI emptying UL buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsDetectedPuschNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration and confirmed by corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsDetectedPuschVolteNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants that are transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs with bearer mapped to QCI with VoIP service type. Reception must be confirmed by corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransNoAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of transmitted unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransPCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransPCellNoAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions. The grants are transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell, and that have no bearer mapped to a QCI with VoIP serviceType.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransVolte
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransVolteNDO
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: New unicast UL grants transmitted during DRX onDuration to UEs that have bearer mapped to QCI with service type VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsTransVolteNoAck
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants not designated for PUSCH data transmissions. The grants are transmitted to UEs that have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsWithDetectedPusch
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants that are confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsWithDetectedPuschPCell
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants transmitted to UEs that use this cell as the primary cell and do not have any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUlGrantsWithDetectedPuschVolte
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unicast UL grants that are transmitted to UEs with any bearer mapped to a QCI with serviceType of VoIP, for which the reception is confirmed by detecting a corresponding PUSCH transmission.

EntityDef.name: pmUnackedUeRelease
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of RRC Connection Releases that are sent by the eNodeB without expecting any acknowledgement.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityRbUlLowSampl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoLTE quality measurements that could not be used to determine the VoLTE quality of a VoLTE session (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) due to insufficient statistics. These measurements are excluded when the VoLTE integrity KPI is calculated.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityRbUlNok
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of unsatisfactory quality.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityRbUlOk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoLTE sessions (radio bearers with serviceType= VOIP) of satisfactory quality.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityUeUlLowSampl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of VoIP quality measurements that can not determine the VoIP satisfaction of a UE due to insufficient statistics. These measurements are excluded when the VoIP integrity KPI is calculated.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityUeUlNok
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of UE that are not satisfied with their VoIP quality.

EntityDef.name: pmVoipQualityUeUlOk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of UE that are satisfied with their VoIP quality.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessAllowed
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with a decision to allow the UE to access WiFi.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessDecisionByWic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with decision information DECISION BY WIC.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessEval
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times eNodeB receives WiFi Access Decision Request message from the MME. MME requests decision to allow or reject UE in connected mode to access WiFi.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessEvalFailLic
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with decision information NO DECISION. This is because the feature for WiFi Mobility is not OPERABLE in the eNodeB.

EntityDef.name: pmWifiAccessRej
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times the eNodeB sends a WiFi Access Decision Response message to the MME with a decision to reject the UE from accessing WiFi.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveDrbDlSumQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of number of DL active DRBs per QCI. A DL DRB is active if there are buffered DL data for the DRB. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP) Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlSectorCarrierDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The counter shows the distribution of DL UEs that are in 1 to N sectors.
[0]: Sum of active DL UEs that is connected to 1 sector [1]: Sum of active DL UEs that is connected to 2 sectors ----- [5]: Sum of active DL UEs that is connected to 6 sectors or more.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeDlSumQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of number of DL active UE per QCI. A DL active UE for a QCI is a UE that has buffered DL data for the QCI. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP) Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlSectorCarrierDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The counter shows the distribution of UL UEs that are in 1 to N sectors.
[0]: Sum of active UL UEs that is connected to 1 sector [1]: Sum of active UL UEs that is connected to 2 sectors ----- [5]: Sum of active UL UEs that is connected to 6 sectors or more.

EntityDef.name: pmActiveUeUlSumLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The sum of number of UL active UE per LCG (Logical Channel Group). An UL active UE for a LCG is a UE that has buffered UL data for the LCG. (Due to implementation, there are either 9052 or 9053 samples per ROP)

EntityDef.name: pmAdjustAccessDynLoadCtrlDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Counter shows the distribution of the Cell Connection Intensity Control for new accesses (RRC Connection Establishment and Handover). 100% means that the Cell Connection Intensity Control is not changed from its maximum value during the ROP period. The counter is only stepped when the optional feature Dynamic Load Control is activated.
PDF Ranges: [0]: [0..5[ % [1]: [5..10[ % [2]: [10..15[ % 8230; [19]: [95..100[ % [20]: 100 %

EntityDef.name: pmCaActDlIeNbSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of activated DL inter-eNodeB (IeNb) external SCells (ESCells) of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Inter-eNodeB carrier aggregation interactions can be through the IeNB-CA feature or the Elastic RAN feature.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have no activated ESCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated ESCell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated ESCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated ESCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated ESCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaActivatedDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of activated downlink SCells of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have no activated SCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have one activated SCell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have two activated SCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have three activated SCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-configured UEs that have four activated SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaAssignedCsSetsDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of channel selection resource sets (CS sets) assigned to UEs sharing this PCell within the HARQ bundling window. PDF: [0]: 1 set [1]: 2 sets 8230; [11]: 12 sets

EntityDef.name: pmCaAssignedPf3ResDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of PUCCH format3 resource sets assigned to UEs sharing this PCell within the HARQ bundling window.
PDF ranges: [0]: 1 set [1]: 2 sets 8230; [11]: 12 sets

EntityDef.name: pmCaCapableDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of supported SCell CCs that support DL, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UEs that are not DL CA-capable at all, that is, PCell only. [1]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus one SCell. [2]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus two SCells. [3]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus three SCells. [4]: Number of UEs that are DL CA-capable of PCell plus four SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaCapableUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of supported SCell CCs, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UEs that are not UL CA-capable at all, that is, PCell only. [1]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus one SCell. [2]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus two SCells. [3]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus three SCells. [4]: Number of UEs that are UL CA-capable of PCell plus four SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredDlIeNbSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
For inter-eNodeB (IeNb) carrier aggregation interactions, records the number of configured DL external SCells (ESCells) of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell. Inter-eNodeB carrier aggregation interactions can be through the IeNB-CA feature or the Elastic RAN feature.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are not configured with any ESCell. Includes CA capable UEs possibly configured with local SCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with one ESCell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with two ESCells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with three ESCells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-capable UEs that are configured with four ESCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of configured DL SCell CCs, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.
PDF ranges: [0] Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are not configured with any SCell. [1]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with one SCell. [2]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with two SCells. [3]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with three SCells. [4]: Number of DL CA-capable UEs that are configured with four SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaConfiguredUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of configured UL SCells of any duplex mode, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UL CA-capable UEs that are not configured with any SCell. [1]: Number of UL CA-capable UEs that are configured with one SCell. [2]: Number of UL CA-capable UEs that are configured with two SCells. [3]: Number of UL CA-capable UEs that are configured with three SCells. [4]: Number of UL CA-capable UEs that are configured with four SCells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaScheduledDlIeNbSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
For inter-eNodeB (IeNb) carrier aggregation interactions, records the mean number of UEs that have data scheduled on a DL external SCell (ESCell), counted by the number of component carriers hosted on external eNodeBs and simultaneously scheduled. UE is considered scheduled for carrier aggregation if the eNodeB has sent a PDCCH assignment indicating a PDSCH assignment. Inter-eNodeB carrier aggregation interactions can be through the IeNB-CA feature or the Elastic RAN feature.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have zero scheduled EScell. Includes scheduling only on PCell or SCells. [1]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have one simultaneously scheduled EScell. [2]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have two simultaneously scheduled EScells. [3]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have three simultaneously scheduled EScells. [4]: Number of carrier aggregation-activated UE that have four simultaneously scheduled EScells.

EntityDef.name: pmCaScheduledDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of UEs that have data scheduled on DL, calculated by number of CCs scheduled simultaneously. UE is considered scheduled on a CC if a PDCCH assignment that indicates a PDSCH transmission on the CC is transmitted.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have one scheduled CC. [1]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have two CCs scheduled simultaneously. [2]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have three CCs scheduled simultaneously. [3]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have four CCs scheduled simultaneously. [4]: Number of DL CA-activated UEs that have five CCs scheduled simultaneously.

EntityDef.name: pmCaScheduledUlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of UEs that have data scheduled on UL, calculated by number of CCs scheduled simultaneously. UE is considered scheduled on a CC if a PDCCH assignment that grants a PUSCH transmission on the CC is transmitted.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UL CA-activated UEs that have one scheduled CC. [1]: Number of UL CA-activated UEs that have two CCs scheduled simultaneously. [2]: Number of UL CA-activated UEs that have three CCs scheduled simultaneously. [3]: Number of UL CA-activated UEs that have four CCs scheduled simultaneously. [4]: Number of UL CA-activated UEs that have five CCs scheduled simultaneously.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttAddedArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:

[0]: N/A (unallowed ARP value) [1]: Sum of added E-RAB Establish Attempts with ARP priority value 1 ... [15]: Sum of added E-RAB Establish Attempts with ARP priority value 15

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttAddedGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of added GBR E-RAB Establishment attempts within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttAddedHoOngoingArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed establishment attempts of added E-RABs due to ongoing handover per ARP Priority Level. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request. Compressed: True.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttAddedHoOngoingQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of failed establishment attempts of added E-RABs due to ongoing handover per QCI. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request. Compressed: True.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttInitGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:

Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttInitQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttRejAdmMsrInitArp

[0]: N/A (unallowed ARP value) [1]: Sum of successful added E-RABs established with ARP priority value 1 ... [15]: Sum of successful added E-RABs established with ARP priority value 15

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccAddedGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of successfully added GBR E-RABs within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccAddedQci

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccInitGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of successful initial GBR E-RAB Establishments within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccInitQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of successful initial E-RAB setup per QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabLevRopStartQci

EntityDef.name: pmErabModAttQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of E-RAB Modify attempts per QCI. Note: since the QCI itself can be modified, if an E-RAB on QCI x is modified to QCI y, bin [x] would be used (and for subsequent E-RAB Modify attempts, bin [y] would be used).

EntityDef.name: pmErabModSuccQci

Compressed: True

Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabQciMax

Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS (per cell per ARP). The counter is stepped if data was present in the UL or DL buffers. Type: Compressed PDF [0]: Sum of active E-RABs released with ARP priority value 0 [1]: Sum of active E-RABs released with ARP priority value 1 8230;. [15]: Sum of active E-RABs released with ARP priority value 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActCdtAutoPnrQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to: - cell down time initiated automatically caused by a partial node restart or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active). Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActCdtAutoQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to: - cell down time initiated automatically or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer . Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActCdtQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to: - cell down time initiated automatically or by manual intervention or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed and that there is data in either the UL or DL buffer. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level. The counter is stepped if data was present in the UL or DL buffers.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHoQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell for each QCI by eNodeB due to handover execution failure and there is data in the UL or DL buffer. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActHprQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to handover preparation and there is data in the UL or DL buffer. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActPeQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell for each QCI, initiated by the160;RBS160;due to160;UE160;pre-emption. Preconditions are that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed and when data is in the160;UL160;or160;DL160;buffer. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of active E-RABs released abnormally per cell per QCI for requests initiated by eNB (per cell per QCI). , except active E-RABs released due to successful HO. An E-RAB is considered to be active when there are data in the DL or UL queues for the E-RAB.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActTnFailQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell for each QCI due to S1 Interface Down, X2 Interface Down or Transport Resource Unavailable. Preconditions are that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed and there is data in the UL or DL buffer. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbActUeLostQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI because contact with the UE is lost. Preconditions are that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed and that there is data in the UL or DL buffer. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS (per cell per ARP). The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers. Type: Compressed PDF [0]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 0 [1]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 1 8230;. [15]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbCdtAutoPnrQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to: - cell down time initiated automatically caused by a partial node restart or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbCdtAutoQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to: - cell down time initiated automatically or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbCdtQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to: - cell down time initiated automatically or by manual intervention or - automated UE recovery. Precondition: Initial Context Establishment procedure must first be successfully completed. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHoQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell for each QCI by eNodeB due to handover execution failure. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbHprQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI due to handover preparation. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbLicQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases for each cell for each QCI initiated by the RBS due to license reject. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbPeQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB Releases for each cell for each QCI, initiated by the RBS due to UE pre-emption. A precondition is that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed. The counter is stepped regardless of whether or not data is lost in the UL or DL buffers. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of E-RABs released abnormally per cell per QCI for requests initiated by eNB.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbTnFailQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases for each cell for each QCI due to S1 Interface Down, X2 Interface Down or Transport Resource Unavailable. A precondition is that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalEnbUeLostQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal E-RAB releases by eNodeB for each cell for each QCI because contact with the UE is lost. A precondition is that procedure Initial Context Establishment is first successfully completed. Compressed: true.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeActArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME considered as abnormal per cell per ARP Level. The counter is stepped if there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active). Type: Compressed PDF [0]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 0 [1]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 1 8230;. [15]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeActGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME considered as abnormal within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level. The counter is stepped if there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (that is active).
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeActQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of E-RAB Releases (per cell per QCI) initiated by the MME considered as abnormal. The counter is stepped if data was lost in either the UL or DL buffers. Type: Compressed PDF [0]: N/A [1]: Abnormal active E-RAB releases for E-RABs with QCI 1 8230;. [255]: Abnormal active E-RAB releases for E-RABs with QCI 255
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAbnormalMmeQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB releases by the MME per QCI with a cause regarded as abnormal. Compressed: True.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAllEnbQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB Releases (per cell per QCI) initiated by the eNB. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelAllMmeQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB Releases (per cell per QCI) initiated by the MME. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelDlInactGapQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of normal E-RAB release per cell per QCI. Bearer release is initiated by MME with normal release cause via S1 message E-RAB Release Command or UE Context Release Command proceeded by inactivity longer than a configurable threshold in DL direction.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeActQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of active E-RABs released per QCI for requests initiated by MME, except active E-RABs released due to successful HO. An E-RAB is considered to be active when there are data in the DL or UL queues for the E-RAB.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME excluding successful handover per cell per ARP Level. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers. Type: Compressed PDF [0]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 0 (unallowed ARP level) [1]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 1 8230;. [15]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by the MME excluding successful handover within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelMmeQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of E-RAB Releases (per cell per QCI) initiated by the MME excluding successful handover. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbActArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of normal E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS (per cell per ARP). The counter is stepped if there was data lost in UL/DL buffers. Type: Compressed PDF [0]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 0 [1]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 1 8230;. [15]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbActQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of active E-RABs released normally (per cell per QCI) for requests initiated by eNB, except active E-RABs released due to successful HO. An E-RAB is considered to be active when there are data in the DL or UL queues for the E-RAB.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of normal E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS. Type: Compressed PDF [0]: [0]: N/A (unallowed ARP value) [1]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 1 .... [15]: Sum of E-RABs released with ARP priority value 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbGbrArp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of normal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by the RBS within this cell, recorded per ARP priority level.
PDF ranges: [0]: N/A (invalid ARP priority level value) [1]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 1 ... [15]: Number of recorded events for ARP priority level 15
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The total number of E-RABs released normally (per cell per QCI) for requests initiated by eNB.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelNormalEnbUserInactivityQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of E-RAB releases by the eNB per QCI due to User inactivity. Compressed: True.

EntityDef.name: pmErabRelUlInactGapQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total number of normal E-RAB release per cell per QCI. Bearer release is initiated by MME with normal release cause via S1 message E-RAB Release Command or UE Context Release Command proceeded by inactivity longer than a configurable threshold in UL direction.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeOutAttQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of handover execution attempt for ERABs per QCI towards target cell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmHoExeOutSuccQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The number of ERABs per QCI that was successfully handovered to the target cell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmInhibitImeisvFeature
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of times IMEISV of UE inhibits a features use, differentiated per feature.
PDF ranges: [0]: Feature 1, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. [1]: Feature 2, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. ... [19]: Feature 20, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmLaaActivatedSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of activated downlink LAA SCells, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have no activated LAA SCells [1]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have one activated LAA SCell [2]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have two activated LAA SCells [3]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have three activated LAA SCells [4]: Number of LAA carrier aggregation configured UEs that have four activated LAA SCells

EntityDef.name: pmLaaCapableDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of supported LAA SCell CCs that support DL, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of UEs that are not DL LAA CA-capable at all, that is, PCell only [1]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus one LAA SCell [2]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus two LAA SCells [3]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus three LAA SCells [4]: Number of UEs that are DL LAA CA-capable of PCell plus four LAA SCells

EntityDef.name: pmLaaChannelSelTrigger
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Counts the causes for search for a new channel.
PDF ranges: Indicates cause for channel selection; [0]: RSSI level above threshold [1]: LBT success rate below threshold [2]: Timer expiry [3]: Radar detected [4]: Externally set (by another source) [5]: Other reason

EntityDef.name: pmLaaConfigurableDlSum
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of configured DL LAA SCell CCs, for UEs that use this cell as their PCell CC.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are not configured with any LAA SCell [1]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with one LAA SCell [2]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with two LAA SCells [3]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with three LAA SCells [4]: Number of DL LAA CA-capable UEs that are configured with four LAA SCells

EntityDef.name: pmLaaSelectedChannel
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Tracks the channel(s) selected by the Dynamic Channel Selection algorithm (PDF).
PDF ranges: Indicates channel selection; [0]: LAA channel 46890 selected [1]: LAA channel 47090 selected [2]: LAA channel 47290 selected [3]: LAA channel 47490 selected [4]: LAA channel 47690 selected [5]: LAA channel 47890 selected [6]: LAA channel 48090 selected [7]: LAA channel 48290 selected [8]: LAA channel 48490 selected [9]: LAA channel 48690 selected [10]: LAA channel 50090 selected [11]: LAA channel 50290 selected [12]: LAA channel 50490 selected [13]: LAA channel 50690 selected [14]: LAA channel 50890 selected [15]: LAA channel 51090 selected [16]: LAA channel 51290 selected [17]: LAA channel 51490 selected [18]: LAA channel 51690 selected [19]: LAA channel 51890 selected [20]: LAA channel 52090 selected [21]: LAA channel 52290 selected [22]: LAA channel 52490 selected [23]: LAA channel 52740 selected [24]: LAA channel 52940 selected [25]: LAA channel 53140 selected [26]: LAA channel 53340 selected [27]: LAA channel 53540 selected [28]: LAA channel 53740 selected [29]: LAA channel 53940 selected [30]: LAA channel 54120 selected [31]: LAA channel 54340 selected Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmLcgThpTimeUlLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL transmission time used for UL DRB Throughput per LCG. It comprises of time periods from when the 5th data transmission is received on Uu until the second last data transmission is received.

EntityDef.name: pmLcgThpVolUlLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The UL volume used for UL DRB Throughput per LCG. It comprises of the MAC SDU volume received on Uu per LCG, excluding the volume received in the first 4 data transmissions and the data transmission emptying the UL buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmMacDrbThpTimeDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC transfer time accumulated over all DRBs with a given QCI in the cell. Aggregates the number of ms in which MAC layer transmission in DL is needed for a DRB with that QCI. This includes buffer waiting times and possible HARQ retransmission delays. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. The DL MAC transfer time over all carriers is registered on PCell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacDrbThpVolDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC SDU transmitted volume accumulated over all DRBs with a given QCI in the cell.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAckNackModeConfig
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of times UEs are configured with a certain DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of times non-carrier aggregation UEs are configured with Bundling as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode [1]: Number of times non-carrier aggregation UEs are configured with Release 8 multiplexing as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode [2]: Number of times non-carrier aggregation UEs are configured with Release 10 multiplexing as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode [3]: Number of times non-carrier aggregation UEs are configured with Format3 as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode [4]: Number of times carrier aggregation UEs are configured with Format3 as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode [5]: Number of times carrier aggregation UEs are configured with Format 1b-cs as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqNonCaDlAnModeMuxDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of subframes scheduled using multiplexing as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode for non-carrier aggregation configured UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: Incremented for the first scheduled TTI in the bundling window [1]: Incremented for the second scheduled TTI in the bundling window [2]: Incremented for the third scheduled TTI in the bundling window [3]: Incremented for the fourth scheduled TTI in the bundling window

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqNonCaDlAnModePf3Distr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of subframes scheduled using format3 as the DL HARQ ACK/NACK feedback mode for non-carrier aggregation configured UEs.
PDF ranges: [0]: Incremented for the first scheduled TTI in the bundling window [1]: Incremented for the second scheduled TTI in the bundling window [2]: Incremented for the third scheduled TTI in the bundling window [3]: Incremented for the fourth scheduled TTI in the bundling window

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlDrxSyncQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs with the corresponding QCI value.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlNoDrxNoSyncQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs with the corresponding QCI value.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlNoDrxSyncQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs with the corresponding QCI value.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLatTimeDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
The DL MAC DRB latency time for each QCI.
When carrier aggregation is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on the primary cell for the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacLcgThpTimeUlLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Transfer time used for UL LCG throughput. Consists of the number of ms in which there is need for transmission for the LCG. Includes buffer delay and time for possible HARQ retransmissions. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transfer time over all carriers is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmMacLcgThpVolUlLcg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Volume used for UL LCG throughput. Consists of the MAC SDU volume received for each LCG. When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. UL MAC transmitted volume over all carriers is registered on PCell.

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlDrxSyncSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state and are included into the DL MAC DRB latency measurements for each QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlNoDrxNoSyncSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state and are included into the DL MAC DRB latency measurements for each QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlNoDrxSyncSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when the UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state and are included into the DL MAC DRB latency measurements for each QCI.
Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacTimeDlSampQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of data bursts used for the DL MAC DRB transfer time and latency measurements for each QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMacUeThpDlDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of DL MAC UE throughput in the cell.
When carrier aggregation is used, a PDCP SDU can be transmitted over multiple cells, PCell or SCells. The DL MAC transfer time and volume over all the carriers is registered on PCell.
PDF ranges: [0]: < 10 kbps [1]: [10..15[ kbps [2]: [15..22[ kbps [3]: [22..45[ kbps [4]: [45..70[ kbps [5]: [70..100[ kbps [6]: [100..150[ kbps [7]: [150..220[ kbps [8]: [220..450[ kbps [9]: [450..700[ kbps [10]: [700..1000[ kbps [11]: [1000..1500[ kbps [12]: [1500..2200[ kbps [13]: [2200..4500[ kbps [14]: [4500..7000[ kbps [15]: [7000..10000[ kbps [16]: [10000..15000[ kbps [17]: [15000..22000[ kbps [18]: [22000..45000[ kbps [19]: [45000..70000[ kbps [20]: [70000..100000[ kbps [21]: [100000..150000[ kbps [22]: [150000..220000[ kbps [23]: [220000..450000[ kbps [24]: >= 450000 kbps

EntityDef.name: pmMaxDeltaSinrDlComp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of the estimated SINR gain caused by interference from neighboring cells within the Downlink Coordinated Multi-Point cluster.
PDF ranges: [0]: =< 1.0 [1]: ]1.0..2.0] [2]: ]2.0..3.0] ... [7]: ]7.0..8.0] [8]: ]8.0..9.0] [9]: ]9.0..10] [10]: ]10.0..15.0] [11]: ]15.0..20] [12]: > 20.0

EntityDef.name: pmModImeisvParamSet
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of times IMEISV of UE causes the application of specific parameter settings for a certain function.
PDF ranges: [0]: Specific parameter setting 1, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. [1]: Specific parameter setting 2, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. ... [19]: Specific parameter setting 20, see UD Differentiated UE Handling. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmMultiUserMimoUlPrbUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of the uplink PRB pair utilization for multi-user MIMO. Total number of used multi-user MIMO PRB pairs divided by available PRB pairs on the PUSCH.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..10[ % [1]: [10..20[ % [2]: [20..30[ % ... [7]: [70..80[ % [8]: [80..90[ % [9]: >= 90 %

EntityDef.name: pmMultiUserMimoUlUePairsDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of the number of UE pairs for uplink multi-user MIMO.
PDF ranges: [0]: 0 UE pair for uplink multi-user MIMO. [1]: 1 UE pair for uplink multi-user MIMO. [2]: 2 UE pairs for uplink multi-user MIMO. ... [14]: 14 UE pairs for uplink multi-user MIMO. [15]: > 14 UE pairs for uplink multi-user MIMO.

EntityDef.name: pmNonCaAssignedPf3ResDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of PUCCH Format3 resource sets assigned to non-carrier aggregation configured UEs within HARQ bundling window.
PDF ranges: [0]: 1 set [1]: 2 sets ... [11]: 12 sets

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceAggregationDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
This counter indicates the distribution of the Physical Downlink Control Channel (PDCCH) Control Channel Element (CCE) aggregation levels selected during the PDCCH allocation phase.
Ranges: [0]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 1 [1]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 2 [2]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 4 [3]: PDCCH CCE aggregation level set to 8

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceUsedDlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of CCEs used for DL grants per QCI. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceUsedUlQci
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of CCEs used for UL grants. All CCEs used for UL grants for a specific UE will be counted on the configured QCI that has the highest priority. This is since the UL grant does not contain any information about what the grant will be used for by the UE. Compressed: True

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCceUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
PDF of % of CCEs utilized compared with total CCEs available (at the maximum CFI permitted by pdcchCfiMode) each subframe, considering bandwidth and antenna configuration. [0]: utilization <= 5% [1]: 5% < utilization <= 10% [2]: 10% < utilization <= 15% [3]: 15% < utilization <= 20% [4]: 20% < utilization <= 25% [5]: 25% < utilization <= 30% [6]: 30% < utilization <= 35% [7]: 35% < utilization <= 40% [8]: 40% < utilization <= 45% [9]: 45% < utilization <= 50% [10]: 50% < utilization <= 55% [11]: 55% < utilization <= 60% [12]: 60% < utilization <= 65% [13]: 65% < utilization <= 70% [14]: 70% < utilization <= 75% [15]: 75% < utilization <= 80% [16]: 80% < utilization <= 85% [17]: 85% < utilization <= 90% [18]: 90% < utilization <= 95% [19]: 95% < utilization <= 100%
In subframes where the number of available CCEs is zero, the lowest bin is incremented.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchCfiUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: PDF of number of subframes each CFI value was assigned [0]: CFI = 1 [1]: CFI = 2 [2]: CFI = 3

EntityDef.name: pmPdcchSym0PwrUtil
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:

EntityDef.name: pmFlexDrbThpTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL transmission time used for DL DRB Throughput. It is comprised of time periods from when the first piece of data in data burst is transmitted until the second last piece of data in data burst is transmitted.
When CA is used, DL transmission time is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabAttAdded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of added E-RAB setup attempts. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabAttAddedGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of added GBR E-RAB Establishment attempts within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabAttAddedHoOngoing
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of failed establishment attempts of added E-RABs due to ongoing handover. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabAttInit
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of initial E-RAB setup attempts. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabAttInitGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of initial GBR E-RAB Establishment attempts within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabSuccAdded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of successfully added E-RABs. Added E-RABs are all E-RABs present in S1 message E-RAB Setup Request.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabSuccAddedGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of successfully added GBR E-RABs within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabEstabSuccInitGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of successful initial GBR E-RAB Establishments within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by eNB.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalEnbAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by eNB. Counter is stepped if data was present in UL or DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalEnbActGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by RBS within this cell. Counter is stepped if data was present in UL or DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalEnbGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by RBS within this cell. Counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal E-RAB releases by MME.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMmeAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by MME. Counter is stepped if data was lost in either UL or DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMmeActGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME within this cell. Counter is stepped if data was present in UL or DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelAbnormalMmeGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of abnormal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by MME excluding successful handover. Counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelMmeGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by MME excluding successful handover within this cell. Counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelNormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of normal E-RAB Releases per cell initiated by eNB.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexErabRelNormalEnbGbr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of normal GBR E-RAB Releases initiated by RBS within this cell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexLcgThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL transmission time used for UL DRB Throughput. It is comprised of time periods from when the 5th data transmission is received on Uu until the second last data transmission is received.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI and ARP are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexLcgThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL volume used for UL DRB Throughput. It is comprised of MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding volume received in the first 4 data transmissions and data transmission emptying UL buffer.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI and ARP are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC DRB latency time.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDlDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDlNoDrxNoSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacLatTimeDlNoDrxSync
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
DL MAC latency time for data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state. It is accumulated over all active DRBs.
When CA is used, DL MAC DRB latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlDrxSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Inactive state and in UL In-sync state and are included into DL MAC DRB latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlNoDrxNoSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL Out-of-sync state and are included into DL MAC DRB latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlNoDrxSyncSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts that arrive when UE is in DRX Active state and in UL In-sync state and are included into DL MAC DRB latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexMacTimeDlSamp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of data bursts used for DL MAC DRB transfer time and latency measurements.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpLatPktTransDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of DRB packets for DL Latency measurements.
When CA is used, DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpLatTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Aggregated DL Latency for measurement period. Effective DL Latency time comprises the time from PDCP DRB SDU entering buffer until the first data has been transmitted to UE.
When CA is used, DL Latency for all component carriers is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpVolDlDrb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total volume (PDCP SDU) that has been transferred (UM and AM) on DRBs in DL.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total volume is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpVolDlDrbLastTTI
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total DL PDCP SDU volume that is transmitted in the last TTI when buffer for DRB is emptied.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total DL PDCP SDU volume is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameter LCG is not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexPdcpVolDlDrbLastTTIUe
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Total DL PDCP SDU volume to UE level that is transmitted in the last TTI when buffer for DRB is emptied.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Total DL PDCP SDU volume is measured on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexUeThpTimeDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Effective DL transport time comprising those periods from when the first part of PDCP SDU of DL buffer was transmitted on Uu until buffer is emptied, excluding TTI emptying buffer.
When CA is used, PDCP SDU can be sent over multiple cells (PCell/SCell(s)). Effective DL transport time is registered on PCell.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexUeThpTimeUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL volume transfer time used for UL UE Throughput. It is comprised of time periods from when the 5th MAC SDU data reception of UL buffer transfer on Uu until buffer is emptied, excluding TTI emptying buffer.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmFlexUeThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
UL DRB volume used for UL UE Throughput. It is comprised of MAC SDU volume received on Uu, excluding volume received in the first 4 data receptions of UL buffer transfer and TTI emptying UL buffer.
Differentiated by filter parameters in MO PmFlexCounterFilter. Filter parameters QCI, ARP and LCG are not applicable.

EntityDef.name: pmCompUlToADiffDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Every time a UE signal is received the time-of-arrival is estimated in each SectorCarrier used for combining. The difference in time-of-arrival between a measurement SectorCarrier and the SectorCarrier MO in all possible pairs of SectorCarriers is calculated.
Each obtained time-of-arrival estimate difference between sectors shall yield one sample in the distribution for both SectorCarriers involved in the comparison.
PDF ranges: [0]: Number of samples =< -24 us [1]: Number of samples in range ]-24..-23] us [2]: Number of samples in range ]-23..-22] us [3]: Number of samples in range ]-22..-21] us ... [46]: Number of samples in range ]21..22] us [47]: Number of samples in range ]22..23] us [48]: Number of samples in range ]23..24] us [49]: Number of samples > 24 us

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownLockAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled).

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownLockMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDownUnlockMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of times the cell has been enabled.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDowntimeAuto
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Length of time the cell has been disabled due to a fault (system has set cell MO OperationalState to Disabled). The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmCellDowntimeMan
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Length of time the cell has been disabled due to: - AdministrativeState of the cell MO or another MO the cell depends on has been set to Locked by the operator or - the operator has performed a reconfiguration request on an Unlocked cell which requires the cell to be taken down temporarily. The counter is only incremented when the RBS is operational.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabAttInit
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of initial E-RAB Establishment attempts. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmErabEstabSuccInit
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful initial E-RAB Establishments. Initial E-RABs are all E-RABs present in the S1 message Initial Context Setup Request.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAckBpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a BPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlAckQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a QPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlNackBpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a BPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmMacHarqDlNackQpsk
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of unsuccessful HARQ transmissions in the downlink direction using a QPSK modulation.

EntityDef.name: pmPagDiscarded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of S1AP Paging messages discarded and not broadcasted in this NB-IoT cell. This counter is a subset of pmPagReceived.

EntityDef.name: pmPagEdrxDiscarded
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of S1AP eDRX Paging messages discarded and not broadcasted in this cell. This counter is a subset of pmPagEdrxReceived.

EntityDef.name: pmPagEdrxReceived
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of S1AP eDRX Paging messages routed to this cell. This counter is a subset of pmPagReceived.

EntityDef.name: pmPagReceived
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Counts the number of S1AP Paging messages routed to this NB-IoT cell.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolDl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the downlink. This counter includes possible padding bits.

EntityDef.name: pmRadioThpVolUl
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total successfully transferred data volume on MAC level in the uplink. This counter includes possible padding bits.

EntityDef.name: pmRrcConnEstabAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of NB-IoT RRC Connection Request attempts.

EntityDef.name: pmRrcConnEstabAttReatt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of RRC Connection Request attempts that are considered as re-attempts.

EntityDef.name: pmRrcConnEstabFailMmeOvlMod
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed RRC Connection Establishments with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Data due to MME overload.

EntityDef.name: pmRrcConnEstabFailMmeOvlMos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed RRC Connection Establishments with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Signaling due to MME overload.

EntityDef.name: pmRrcConnEstabSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful NB-IoT RRC Connection Establishments.

EntityDef.name: pmS1SigConnEstabAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: This measurement provides the number of S1 Signaling connection establishment attempts for any establishment cause.

EntityDef.name: pmS1SigConnEstabFailMmeOvlMos
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of failed S1 signaling connection establishments with Establishment cause Mobile Originating Signaling due to MME overload.

EntityDef.name: pmS1SigConnEstabSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of successful S1 signaling connection establishments.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context Releases initiated by the RBS.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Contexts Releases initiated by the RBS and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbActUeLost
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context releases by the RBS due that the radio connection with the NB-IoT device is lost and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalEnbUeLost
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of abnormal UE Context releases by the eNB due to that the radio connection with the NB-IoT device is lost.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of UE Context Releases by the MME with a cause regarded as abnormal.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelAbnormalMmeAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of UE Context Releases initiated by the MME with a cause regarded as abnormal and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of UE Context Releases initiated by the MME. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelMmeAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of UE Context Releases initiated by the MME and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelNormalEnb
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of normal UE Context Releases triggered by RBS. The counter is stepped regardless of whether data was or was not lost in UL/DL buffers.

EntityDef.name: pmUeCtxtRelNormalEnbAct
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of normal UE Context Releases triggered by RBS and that there was data in either the UL or DL buffer (i.e. active).

EntityDef.name: pmRaMsg2AttNbCbra

EntityDef.name: pmRaSuccNbCbra

EntityDef.name: pmLicDlCapDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Shows the utilization of DL baseband capacity relative to the minimum of installed license for DL Baseband Capacity or hardware capacity limit. Expressed as percentage of the minimum of license limit or hardware capacity limit.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..5]%, [1]: ]5..10]%, [2]: ]10..15]%, [3]: ]15..20]%, [4]: ]20..25]%, [5]: ]25..30]%, [6]: ]30..35]%, [7]: ]35..40]%, [8]: ]40..45]%, [9]: ]45..50]%, [10]: ]50..55]%, [11]: ]55..60]%, [12]: ]60..65]%, [13]: ]65..70]%, [14]: ]70..75]%, [15]: ]75..80]%, [16]: ]80..85]%, [17]: ]85..90]%, [18]: ]90..95]%, [19]: ]95..100]%
Note: 0 on all bins is a reserved value set that indicates the cell has been disabled for the entire ROP. If cell is active, no utilization has occurred for the entire ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmLicDlPrbCapDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Shows the utilization of DL PRB capacity relative to the minimum of installed license for DL PRB Capacity or hardware PRB capacity limit. Expressed as percentage of the minimum of license limit or hardware PRB capacity limit.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..5]%, [1]: ]5..10]%, [2]: ]10..15]%, [3]: ]15..20]%, [4]: ]20..25]%, [5]: ]25..30]%, [6]: ]30..35]%, [7]: ]35..40]%, [8]: ]40..45]%, [9]: ]45..50]%, [10]: ]50..55]%, [11]: ]55..60]%, [12]: ]60..65]%, [13]: ]65..70]%, [14]: ]70..75]%, [15]: ]75..80]%, [16]: ]80..85]%, [17]: ]85..90]%, [18]: ]90..95]%, [19]: ]95..100]%
Note: 0 on all bins is a reserved value set that indicates the cell has been disabled for the entire ROP. If cell is active, no utilization has occurred for the entire ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmLicDlPrbUsedDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of DL PRB capacity usages with configured bin step size. Y represents PRB license unit. It comes from BbProcessingResource::pmLicPrbUnit.
PDF ranges: [0]: From 0 to Y PRBs ... [n]: From (n*Y)+1 to (n+1)*Y PRBs ... [47]: Above 47*Y+1 PRBs

EntityDef.name: pmLicUlCapDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Shows the utilization of UL baseband capacity relative to the minimum of installed license for UL Baseband Capacity or hardware capacity limit. Expressed as percentage of the minimum of license limit or hardware capacity limit.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..5]%, [1]: ]5..10]%, [2]: ]10..15]%, [3]: ]15..20]%, [4]: ]20..25]%, [5]: ]25..30]%, [6]: ]30..35]%, [7]: ]35..40]%, [8]: ]40..45]%, [9]: ]45..50]%, [10]: ]50..55]%, [11]: ]55..60]%, [12]: ]60..65]%, [13]: ]65..70]%, [14]: ]70..75]%, [15]: ]75..80]%, [16]: ]80..85]%, [17]: ]85..90]%, [18]: ]90..95]%, [19]: ]95..100]%
Note: 0 on all bins is a reserved value set that indicates the cell has been disabled for the entire ROP. If cell is active, no utilization has occurred for the entire ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmLicUlPrbCapDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Shows the utilization of UL PRB capacity relative to the minimum of installed license for UL PRB Capacity or hardware PRB capacity limit. Expressed as percentage of the minimum of license limit or hardware PRB capacity limit.
PDF ranges: [0]: [0..5]%, [1]: ]5..10]%, [2]: ]10..15]%, [3]: ]15..20]%, [4]: ]20..25]%, [5]: ]25..30]%, [6]: ]30..35]%, [7]: ]35..40]%, [8]: ]40..45]%, [9]: ]45..50]%, [10]: ]50..55]%, [11]: ]55..60]%, [12]: ]60..65]%, [13]: ]65..70]%, [14]: ]70..75]%, [15]: ]75..80]%, [16]: ]80..85]%, [17]: ]85..90]%, [18]: ]90..95]%, [19]: ]95..100]%
Note: 0 on all bins is a reserved value set that indicates the cell has been disabled for the entire ROP. If cell is active, no utilization has occurred for the entire ROP.

EntityDef.name: pmLicUlPrbUsedDistr
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Distribution of UL PRB capacity usages with configured bin step size. Y represents PRB license unit. It comes from BbProcessingResource::pmLicPrbUnit.
PDF ranges: [0]: From 0 to Y PRBs ... [n]: From (n*Y)+1 to (n+1)*Y PRBs ... [47]: Above 47*Y+1 PRBs

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlEth

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlEthFormat
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of downlink DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in the Ethernet part of the RBS due to that DL consistency check fails.

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlEthX2Fwd

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlNoMbmsCtxt

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscDlNoUeCtxt

EntityDef.name: pmPdcpPktDiscUlEthPacing
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of uplink DRB packets (PDCP SDUs) discarded in the Ethernet part of the RBS due UL pacing functionality.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionEnd
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times an MBMS session is stopped by MBMS session duration timeout.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionEstabAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of MBMS session establishment attempts. It is incremented each time the MBMS SESSION START REQUEST is received.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionEstabFailNotSupp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of MBMS sessions that have failed to be established due to unsupported configuration in eNodeB. It is incremented each time the MBMS SESSION START FAILURE is sent.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionEstabFailUpdate
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times an MBMS session start fails due to unsupported MBMS session parameter update. It is incremented each time the MBMS SESSION START FAILURE is sent for an already started session.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionEstabSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times an MBMS session is successfully established in the eNodeB. It is incremented each time the MBMS SESSION START RESPONSE is sent.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionStopAuditTimer
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times an MBMS session is stopped by the MBMS audit timer.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionStopMme
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times an MBMS session is stopped by a received MBMS SESSION STOP REQUEST message.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionStopMmeNoSession
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times the eNodeB receives the MBMS SESSION STOP REQUEST message for an MBMS session that is already stopped.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionUpdateAtt
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of MBMS session update attempts. It is incremented each time the MBMS SESSION UPDATE REQUEST is received.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionUpdateFailNotSupp
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total failures of MBMS session update caused by unsupported eNodeB configuration.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionUpdateFailParam
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Total failures of MBMS session update caused by unsupported MBMS session update parameter.

EntityDef.name: pmMbmsSessionUpdateSucc
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The total number of times an MBMS session update is successfully handled in the eNodeB. It is incremented each time the MBMS SESSION UPDATE RESPONSE is sent.
