EntityDef.name: pmSctpAborted
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from any state, using the chunk ABORT.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpActiveEstab
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition to the ESTABLISHED state from the COOKIE-ECHOED state.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpCurrEstab
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of SCTP associations for which the current state is either ESTABLISHED, SHUTDOWN-PENDING, or SHUTDOWN-RECEIVED.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpInErrors
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received SCTP datagrams for which an SCTP association could not be determined.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpInNoPorts
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: The number of received SCTP datagrams for which an SCTP association and endpoint could not be determined (for example if there was no user application at the destination port).

EntityDef.name: pmSctpPassiveEstab
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition from the CLOSED state to the ESTABLISHED state.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpShutdowns
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the SHUTDOWN-SENT state or the SHUTDOWN-ACK-SENT state.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatAssocOutOfBlue
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of out-of-the-blue packets that are received by the host.
These are SCTP packets that are correctly formed (with a correct checksum), but where the receiver is not able to identify the association to which this packet belongs.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatChecksumErrorCounter
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of SCTP packets received from the peers, with an invalid checksum.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatCommResume
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times SCTP has sent a congestion ceased indication to the user.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatCommStop
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times SCTP has sent a congestion indication to the user.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatFragmentedUserMsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of fragmented user messages, incremented when the first data chunk of fragmented message is sent.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatOutOfOrderRecChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of unordered chunks received from the peers.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatOutOfOrderSendChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of unordered chunks transmitted to the peers.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatReassembledUserMsg
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of reassembled user messages, incremented when the first data chunk of a fragmented message is received.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatRecChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of received DATA chunks.
The counter does NOT include abnormal or discarded chunks.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatRecChunksDropped
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received chunks dropped for the following reasons: - Invalid association state - Duplicated data - Invalid stream identity in the DATA_CHUNK - Invalid verification tag in the packet - Stale SACK_CHUNK received - Lack of receiving buffer - ULP buffer overflow.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatReceivedControlChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of received control chunks.
The counter does not include abnormal or discarded chunks.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatReceivedPackages
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received packets, including duplicates and those received in error.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatRetransChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of DATA chunks retransmitted to the peers.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatSentChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transmitted DATA chunks (excluding retransmissions).

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatSentChunksDropped
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of outgoing user messages originating from the application for this SCTP for which no problems were encountered to prevent their transmission but were discarded. User messages are discarded due to lack of M-buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatSentControlChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transmitted control chunks.

EntityDef.name: pmSctpStatSentPackages
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transmitted packets.

EntityDef.name: pmAborteds
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that the association has become unavailable to the SCTP user due to ungraceful termination by the local or the remote side, using the chunk ABORT.Ungraceful termination during association establishment does not increment this counter.

EntityDef.name: pmCongestions
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that the local transmission buffer for the association is congested.

EntityDef.name: pmInControlChunkAbnormal
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received control chunks which were chosen to be discarded due to errors in the chunk format or in the chunk content.

EntityDef.name: pmInControlChunkDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received control chunks which were discarded even though no errors were detected. Chunks can be discarded for the following reasons: - unsupported chunk type. - wrong association state.

EntityDef.name: pmInControlChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of received control chunks.
The counter does not include abnormal or discarded chunks.

EntityDef.name: pmInDataChunkAbnormal
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received DATA chunks with errors in the chunk format or in the chunk contents preventing them from being delivered to the SCTP user.

EntityDef.name: pmInDataChunkDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received DATA chunks that were discarded due to lack of space in the receive buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmInDataChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of received DATA chunks.
The counter does NOT include abnormal or discarded chunks.

EntityDef.name: pmInOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of octets in received packets for this association, including duplicates and those received in error.

EntityDef.name: pmInPacks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of received packets for this association, including duplicates and those received in error.

EntityDef.name: pmOutControlChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transmitted control chunks.

EntityDef.name: pmOutDataChunkDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of outgoing DATA chunks for this association for which no problems were encountered to prevent their transmission but were discarded. DATA chunks are discarded due to ungraceful closing of the association.

EntityDef.name: pmOutDataChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transmitted DATA chunks (excluding retransmissions).

EntityDef.name: pmOutOctets
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of octets in transmitted packets.

EntityDef.name: pmOutPacks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of transmitted packets.

EntityDef.name: pmOutUserMsgDiscards
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of outgoing user data messages, which were discarded even though no problems were encountered to prevent their transmission. User messages are discarded due to lack of space in the transmission buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmPeerZeroWindows
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that the association has started the zero window supervision procedure.

EntityDef.name: pmRtxChunks
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of retransmitted DATA chunks.

EntityDef.name: pmShutdowns
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of times that the association has become unavailable to the SCTP user due to graceful shutdown by the local or the remote side.

EntityDef.name: pmTimeCongested
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of seconds that the local transmission buffer for the association is congested.

EntityDef.name: pmTimePeerZeroWindow
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of seconds that the remote peer has claimed to have zero window for its receive buffer.

EntityDef.name: pmTimeUnavail
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION: Number of seconds the association has been unavailable to the SCTP user.

EntityDef.name: pmUnavailRetrans
EntityDef.DESCRIPTION:
Number of times that the association has become unavailable to the SCTP user because all paths forming part of this association became inactive for one of the following reasons:
- Retransmission limit was reached - an ICMP message is received and is treated as if the retransmission limit was reached
